1
00:00:59,869 --> 00:01:01,996
Yes, Marlin.

2
00:01:02,038 --> 00:01:04,131
No, I see it. It's beautiful.

3
00:01:04,174 --> 00:01:06,699
So, Coral, when you said
you wanted an ocean view...

4
00:01:06,743 --> 00:01:10,907
you didn't think you'd get
the whole ocean, did you?

5
00:01:10,947 --> 00:01:15,748
Oh, yeah.
A fish can breathe out here.

6
00:01:15,785 --> 00:01:17,719
Did your man deliver,
or did he deliver?

7
00:01:17,754 --> 00:01:20,052
- My man delivered.
- And it wasn't so easy.

8
00:01:20,090 --> 00:01:23,389
Because a lot of other clownfish
had their eyes on this place.

9
00:01:23,426 --> 00:01:25,860
You better believe they did...
every single one of them.

10
00:01:25,895 --> 00:01:27,920
You did good.

11
00:01:27,964 --> 00:01:30,592
And the neighborhood
is awesome.

12
00:01:40,610 --> 00:01:42,271
So, you do like it, don't you?

13
00:01:42,312 --> 00:01:45,770
No, no. I do, I do.
I really do like it.

14
00:01:45,815 --> 00:01:48,750
But, Marlin, I know that
the drop off is desirable...

15
00:01:48,785 --> 00:01:51,049
with the great schools
and the amazing view...

16
00:01:51,087 --> 00:01:53,156
but do we really need
so much space?

17
00:01:53,189 --> 00:01:55,987
Coral, honey, these are our kids
we're talking about.

18
00:01:56,026 --> 00:01:58,187
They deserve the best.
Look, look, look.

19
00:01:58,228 --> 00:02:00,458
They'll wake up,
poke their little heads out...

20
00:02:00,497 --> 00:02:03,564
and they see a whale!
Right by their bedroom window.

21
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:05,898
You'll wake the kids.

22
00:02:05,935 --> 00:02:07,732
Oh, right, right.

23
00:02:11,474 --> 00:02:16,241
Aw, look. They're dreaming.

24
00:02:16,279 --> 00:02:18,440
We still have to name them.

25
00:02:18,481 --> 00:02:20,244
You want to name
all of them right now?

26
00:02:20,283 --> 00:02:23,548
All right, we'll name
this half Marlin Junior...

27
00:02:23,586 --> 00:02:25,713
and this half Coral Junior.

28
00:02:25,755 --> 00:02:28,315
- OK, we're done.
- I like Nemo.

29
00:02:28,358 --> 00:02:31,122
Nemo. We'll name one Nemo...

30
00:02:31,161 --> 00:02:33,721
but I'd like most of them
to be Marlin Junior.

31
00:02:33,763 --> 00:02:35,128
Just think,
in a couple of days...

32
00:02:35,165 --> 00:02:38,657
- we're going to be parents.
- Yeah.

33
00:02:38,701 --> 00:02:40,328
What if they don't like me?

34
00:02:40,370 --> 00:02:41,894
- Marlin.
- No, really.

35
00:02:41,938 --> 00:02:46,898
There's over 400 eggs.
Odds are, one will like you.

36
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,240
What?

37
00:02:51,281 --> 00:02:54,910
- You remember how we met?
- I try not to.

38
00:02:54,951 --> 00:02:56,418
Well, I remember.
"Excuse me, miss..."

39
00:02:56,453 --> 00:02:58,921
"can you check and see
if I have a hook in my lip?"

40
00:02:58,955 --> 00:03:01,321
You got a little closer
because it was wiggling.

41
00:03:01,357 --> 00:03:04,485
- Get away, get away!
- Here he is. Cutie's here.

42
00:03:06,362 --> 00:03:08,455
Where did everybody go?

43
00:03:15,238 --> 00:03:17,331
Coral, get inside the house.

44
00:03:18,875 --> 00:03:21,275
No, Coral, don't.
They'll be fine.

45
00:03:21,311 --> 00:03:23,905
Just get inside...
You, right now.

46
00:03:26,683 --> 00:03:28,548
No!

47
00:03:47,070 --> 00:03:48,332
Coral!

48
00:03:53,843 --> 00:03:55,811
Coral?

49
00:03:57,981 --> 00:03:59,312
Coral?

50
00:04:06,189 --> 00:04:07,451
Coral?

51
00:04:09,893 --> 00:04:11,224
Coral?

52
00:04:17,233 --> 00:04:18,928
Coral?

53
00:04:41,658 --> 00:04:43,489
There, there, there.

54
00:04:43,526 --> 00:04:46,017
It's OK. Daddy's here.

55
00:04:47,263 --> 00:04:48,924
Daddy's got you.

56
00:04:51,768 --> 00:04:56,296
I promise, I will never
let anything happen to you...

57
00:04:56,339 --> 00:04:58,102
Nemo.

58
00:05:34,577 --> 00:05:37,012
First day of school!

59
00:05:37,013 --> 00:05:39,811
Wake up, wake up!
First day of school.

60
00:05:39,849 --> 00:05:42,340
I don't want to go to school...
five more minutes.

61
00:05:42,385 --> 00:05:43,647
Not you, Dad, me.

62
00:05:43,686 --> 00:05:45,085
- OK?
- Get up, get up.

63
00:05:45,121 --> 00:05:47,817
It's time for school,
time for school.

64
00:05:47,857 --> 00:05:49,415
All right, I'm up.

65
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:52,889
- Nemo!
- First day of school!

66
00:05:52,929 --> 00:05:55,090
Nemo, don't move.

67
00:05:55,131 --> 00:05:56,530
You'll never get out
of there yourself.

68
00:05:56,566 --> 00:05:58,727
I'll do it.

69
00:05:58,768 --> 00:06:00,736
- You feel a break?
- No.

70
00:06:00,770 --> 00:06:02,499
Sometimes you can't tell
'cause fluid rushes to the area.

71
00:06:02,538 --> 00:06:04,733
- Are you woozy?
- No.

72
00:06:04,774 --> 00:06:07,038
- How many stripes do I have?
- I'm fine.

73
00:06:07,076 --> 00:06:08,873
- Answer the stripe question.
- Three.

74
00:06:08,911 --> 00:06:10,378
No! See?
Something's wrong with you.

75
00:06:10,413 --> 00:06:13,211
I have one, two, three...
That's all I have?

76
00:06:13,249 --> 00:06:16,150
You're OK. How's the lucky fin?

77
00:06:16,185 --> 00:06:18,983
- Lucky.
- Let's see.

78
00:06:20,456 --> 00:06:21,946
Are you sure you want to go
to school this year?

79
00:06:21,991 --> 00:06:24,892
There's no problem if you don't.
You can wait 5 or 6 years.

80
00:06:24,927 --> 00:06:26,792
Come on, Dad,
it's time for school.

81
00:06:26,829 --> 00:06:29,491
Forgot to brush.

82
00:06:29,532 --> 00:06:31,523
Do you want this anemone
to sting you?

83
00:06:31,567 --> 00:06:33,967
- Yes.
- Brush.

84
00:06:34,003 --> 00:06:35,664
- OK, I'm done.
- You missed a spot.

85
00:06:36,005 --> 00:06:37,666
- Where?
- There.

86
00:06:37,707 --> 00:06:40,676
Right there. And here and here.

87
00:06:49,652 --> 00:06:50,812
All right, we're excited.

88
00:06:50,853 --> 00:06:52,616
The first day of school.
Here we go.

89
00:06:52,655 --> 00:06:54,623
We're ready to learn
to get some knowledge.

90
00:06:54,657 --> 00:06:57,057
What's the one thing we have
to remember about the ocean?

91
00:06:57,093 --> 00:06:59,527
- It's not safe.
- That's my boy.

92
00:06:59,562 --> 00:07:01,826
First, we check to see
that the coast is clear.

93
00:07:01,864 --> 00:07:04,264
We go out... and back in.

94
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:06,598
And then we go out...
and back in.

95
00:07:06,636 --> 00:07:09,662
And then one more time...
out and back in.

96
00:07:09,706 --> 00:07:11,537
And sometimes, if you want
to do it four times...

97
00:07:11,574 --> 00:07:13,940
- Dad...
- All right, come on, boy.

98
00:07:16,646 --> 00:07:19,740
Maybe while I'm at school,
I'll see a shark.

99
00:07:19,782 --> 00:07:22,444
- I highly doubt that.
- Have you ever met a shark?

100
00:07:22,485 --> 00:07:24,146
No, and I don't plan to.

101
00:07:24,187 --> 00:07:27,384
- How old are sea turtles?
- I don't know.

102
00:07:27,423 --> 00:07:29,118
Sandy Plankton
from next door...

103
00:07:29,158 --> 00:07:32,060
he says that sea turtles live
to be about 100 years old.

104
00:07:32,061 --> 00:07:34,495
He says that sea turtles live
to be about 100 years old.

105
00:07:34,530 --> 00:07:36,794
If I ever meet a sea turtle,
I'll ask him.

106
00:07:36,833 --> 00:07:38,767
After I'm done
talking to the shark, OK?

107
00:07:38,801 --> 00:07:42,370
Hold on. Wait to cross.

108
00:07:42,438 --> 00:07:44,633
Hold my fin.

109
00:07:44,674 --> 00:07:46,005
Dad, you're not
going to freak out...

110
00:07:46,042 --> 00:07:48,033
like you did at
the petting zoo, are you?

111
00:07:48,077 --> 00:07:50,841
That snail was about to charge.

112
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:53,314
I wonder where
we're supposed to go.

113
00:07:53,349 --> 00:07:54,839
Bye, Mom!

114
00:07:54,884 --> 00:07:56,977
I'll pick you up after school.

115
00:07:58,755 --> 00:08:01,815
Come on, you guys, stop it!
Give it back!

116
00:08:01,858 --> 00:08:04,850
Come on, we'll try over there.

117
00:08:06,195 --> 00:08:08,254
Excuse me, is this where
we meet his teacher?

118
00:08:08,297 --> 00:08:10,822
Well, look who's out
of the anemone.

119
00:08:10,867 --> 00:08:12,067
Yes. Shocking, I know.

120
00:08:12,101 --> 00:08:13,864
- Marty, right?
- Marlin.

121
00:08:13,903 --> 00:08:15,063
- Bob.
- Ted.

122
00:08:15,104 --> 00:08:17,095
Bill. Hey, you're a clownfish.

123
00:08:17,140 --> 00:08:19,700
You're funny, right?
Tell us a joke.

124
00:08:19,742 --> 00:08:21,039
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

125
00:08:21,077 --> 00:08:23,978
Well, actually,
that's a common misconception.

126
00:08:24,013 --> 00:08:26,538
Clownfish are no funnier
than any other fish.

127
00:08:26,582 --> 00:08:28,573
- Come on, clownie.
- Do something funny.

128
00:08:28,618 --> 00:08:31,086
All right, I know one joke.

129
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:35,181
There's a mollusk, see?
And he walks up to a sea...

130
00:08:35,224 --> 00:08:37,283
He doesn't walk up,
he swims up.

131
00:08:37,326 --> 00:08:39,191
Actually,
the mollusk isn't moving.

132
00:08:39,228 --> 00:08:42,789
He's in one place,
and then the sea cucumber...

133
00:08:42,832 --> 00:08:44,299
Well, they... I'm mixed up.

134
00:08:44,333 --> 00:08:47,063
There was a mollusk
and a sea cucumber.

135
00:08:47,103 --> 00:08:48,704
None of them were walking,
so forget that I...

136
00:08:48,705 --> 00:08:51,935
Sheldon! Get out of
Mr. Johannsen's yard now!

137
00:08:51,974 --> 00:08:54,340
All right, you kids!

138
00:08:54,377 --> 00:08:57,437
Where'd you go?

139
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:59,641
Dad, can I go play, too? Can I?

140
00:08:59,682 --> 00:09:02,674
I would feel better if
you'd play on the sponge beds.

141
00:09:07,256 --> 00:09:09,224
That's where I would play.

142
00:09:10,860 --> 00:09:13,294
- What's wrong with his fin?
- He looks funny.

143
00:09:13,329 --> 00:09:15,695
Hey, what'd I do?

144
00:09:15,731 --> 00:09:17,699
Be nice.
It's his first time at school.

145
00:09:17,733 --> 00:09:20,429
He was born with it.
We call it his lucky fin.

146
00:09:20,536 --> 00:09:22,731
- Dad...
- See this tentacle?

147
00:09:22,772 --> 00:09:24,899
It's actually shorter
than all my other tentacles...

148
00:09:24,941 --> 00:09:27,068
but you can't really tell.

149
00:09:27,109 --> 00:09:29,543
Especially when
I twirl them like this.

150
00:09:29,579 --> 00:09:31,638
I'm H-2-O intolerant.

151
00:09:31,681 --> 00:09:33,649
I'm obnoxious.

152
00:09:35,284 --> 00:09:38,117
Let's name the zones,
the zones, the zones

153
00:09:38,154 --> 00:09:41,317
Let's name
the zones of the open sea

154
00:09:41,357 --> 00:09:42,551
Mr. Ray!

155
00:09:42,592 --> 00:09:45,493
- Come on, Nemo.
- You better stay with me.

156
00:09:45,528 --> 00:09:47,393
Mesopelagic, bathyal,
abyssalpelagic

157
00:09:47,430 --> 00:09:50,866
All the rest are too deep
for you and me to see

158
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:54,233
I wonder where
my class has gone?

159
00:09:54,270 --> 00:09:55,999
We're under here!

160
00:09:56,038 --> 00:09:57,903
Oh, there you are.

161
00:09:57,940 --> 00:09:59,498
Climb aboard, explorers.

162
00:09:59,542 --> 00:10:00,839
Oh, knowledge exploring

163
00:10:00,877 --> 00:10:02,367
is, oh, so lyrical

164
00:10:02,411 --> 00:10:04,845
When you think thoughts
that are empirical

165
00:10:04,881 --> 00:10:06,041
Dad, you can go now.

166
00:10:06,082 --> 00:10:09,176
- Hello. Who is this?
- I'm Nemo.

167
00:10:09,218 --> 00:10:12,881
Nemo, all new explorers
must answer a science question.

168
00:10:12,922 --> 00:10:15,720
- OK.
- You live in what kind of home?

169
00:10:15,758 --> 00:10:17,453
An anemon-none.

170
00:10:17,493 --> 00:10:19,484
A nemenem-menome.

171
00:10:19,529 --> 00:10:22,555
OK, don't hurt yourself.
Welcome aboard, explorers.

172
00:10:22,598 --> 00:10:24,532
Just so you know,
he's got a little fin.

173
00:10:24,567 --> 00:10:26,228
I find if he's having
trouble swimming...

174
00:10:26,269 --> 00:10:28,237
I let him take a break,
10, 15 minutes.

175
00:10:28,271 --> 00:10:30,705
Dad, it's time
for you to go now.

176
00:10:30,740 --> 00:10:32,799
Don't worry. We're gonna
stay together as a group.

177
00:10:32,842 --> 00:10:35,242
OK, class,
optical orbits up front.

178
00:10:35,278 --> 00:10:38,270
And remember, we keep
our supraesophogeal ganglion...

179
00:10:38,314 --> 00:10:40,748
to ourselves.
That means you, Jimmy.

180
00:10:40,883 --> 00:10:42,748
Aw, man!

181
00:10:42,785 --> 00:10:44,810
Bye, Nemo!

182
00:10:44,854 --> 00:10:46,253
Bye, Dad!

183
00:10:46,289 --> 00:10:47,950
Bye, son!

184
00:10:50,159 --> 00:10:51,956
Be safe.

185
00:10:51,994 --> 00:10:54,554
You're doing pretty well
for a first-timer.

186
00:10:54,597 --> 00:10:56,929
You can't hold on to them
forever, can you?

187
00:10:56,966 --> 00:10:59,196
I had a tough time with
my oldest out at the drop off.

188
00:10:59,235 --> 00:11:01,499
They got to grow up...
The drop off?

189
00:11:01,537 --> 00:11:04,404
They're going to the drop off?
What are you, insane?

190
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:07,739
Why don't we fry them up now
and serve them with chips?

191
00:11:07,777 --> 00:11:09,039
Hey, Marty, calm down.

192
00:11:09,078 --> 00:11:11,342
Don't tell me
to be calm, pony boy.

193
00:11:11,380 --> 00:11:13,678
Pony boy?

194
00:11:13,716 --> 00:11:16,583
For a clownfish,
he really isn't that funny.

195
00:11:16,619 --> 00:11:18,018
Pity.

196
00:11:19,956 --> 00:11:22,516
Let's name the species,
the species, the species

197
00:11:22,558 --> 00:11:23,855
Let's name the species
that live in the sea

198
00:11:25,094 --> 00:11:26,891
There's

199
00:11:26,929 --> 00:11:28,988
Porifera, coelenterata,
hydrozoa, scyphozoa

200
00:11:29,031 --> 00:11:31,090
Anthozoa, ctenophora,
bryozoas, three

201
00:11:31,133 --> 00:11:33,795
Gastropoda, arthropoda,
echinoderma

202
00:11:33,836 --> 00:11:35,133
And some fish like you and me

203
00:11:35,171 --> 00:11:36,502
Come on, sing with me.

204
00:11:43,746 --> 00:11:45,611
Just the girls this time.

205
00:11:45,648 --> 00:11:47,616
Oh, seaweed is cool

206
00:11:47,650 --> 00:11:48,912
Seaweed is fun

207
00:11:48,951 --> 00:11:50,418
it makes its food

208
00:11:53,723 --> 00:11:55,748
OK, the drop off.

209
00:11:55,791 --> 00:11:58,055
All right, kids,
feel free to explore...

210
00:11:58,094 --> 00:11:59,254
but stay close.

211
00:11:59,295 --> 00:12:01,490
Stromalitic cyanobacteria! Gather.

212
00:12:02,832 --> 00:12:05,562
An entire ecosystem contained
in one infinitesimal speck.

213
00:12:05,601 --> 00:12:07,262
There are as many protein pairs
contained in this...

214
00:12:07,303 --> 00:12:09,737
Come on, let's go.

215
00:12:09,772 --> 00:12:11,137
Come on, sing with me!

216
00:12:11,173 --> 00:12:13,437
There's porifera, coelenterata

217
00:12:13,476 --> 00:12:14,943
Hydrozoa, scyphozoa

218
00:12:14,977 --> 00:12:16,545
Anthozoa, ctenophora,
bryozoas, three

219
00:12:16,546 --> 00:12:19,605
Hey, guys, wait up!

220
00:12:24,553 --> 00:12:26,646
Cool.

221
00:12:28,324 --> 00:12:29,951
Saved your life!

222
00:12:29,992 --> 00:12:32,324
Aw, you guys made me ink.

223
00:12:33,763 --> 00:12:35,196
What's that?

224
00:12:36,632 --> 00:12:39,658
I know what that is.
Sandy Plankton saw one.

225
00:12:39,702 --> 00:12:42,796
He said it was called a butt.

226
00:12:44,306 --> 00:12:46,604
That's a pretty big butt.

227
00:12:48,077 --> 00:12:51,274
Oh, look at me.
I'm going to touch the butt.

228
00:12:53,816 --> 00:12:56,614
Oh, yeah?
Let's see you get closer.

229
00:12:56,652 --> 00:12:58,279
OK.

230
00:12:58,320 --> 00:13:00,811
Beat that.

231
00:13:00,856 --> 00:13:03,381
Come on, Nemo.
How far can you go?

232
00:13:03,426 --> 00:13:05,894
My dad says it's not safe.

233
00:13:05,928 --> 00:13:08,863
- Nemo! No!
- Dad?

234
00:13:08,898 --> 00:13:10,331
You were about
to swim into open water.

235
00:13:10,366 --> 00:13:11,594
No, I wasn't...

236
00:13:11,634 --> 00:13:13,465
Good thing I was here.
If I hadn't shown up...

237
00:13:13,502 --> 00:13:15,766
- He wasn't going to go.
- He was too afraid.

238
00:13:15,805 --> 00:13:17,102
No, I wasn't.

239
00:13:17,139 --> 00:13:18,572
This does not
concern you, kids...

240
00:13:18,607 --> 00:13:20,973
and you're lucky
I don't tell your parents.

241
00:13:21,010 --> 00:13:22,307
You know you can't swim well.

242
00:13:22,344 --> 00:13:24,278
I can swim fine, Dad, OK?

243
00:13:24,313 --> 00:13:27,214
No, it's not OK.
You shouldn't be near here.

244
00:13:27,249 --> 00:13:29,649
OK, I was right. You'll start
school in a year or two.

245
00:13:29,685 --> 00:13:32,415
No, Dad! Just because
you're scared of the ocean...

246
00:13:32,455 --> 00:13:33,622
Clearly, you're not ready...

247
00:13:33,656 --> 00:13:34,816
and you're not coming back
until you are.

248
00:13:34,857 --> 00:13:36,119
You think
you can do these things...

249
00:13:36,158 --> 00:13:38,058
but you just can't, Nemo!

250
00:13:39,395 --> 00:13:40,987
I hate you.

251
00:13:42,198 --> 00:13:44,826
There's

252
00:13:44,867 --> 00:13:46,698
Nothing to see.
Gather. Over there.

253
00:13:46,736 --> 00:13:47,998
Excuse me.
Is there anything I can do?

254
00:13:48,037 --> 00:13:50,096
I am a scientist, sir.
Is there any problem?

255
00:13:50,139 --> 00:13:52,232
I'm sorry. I didn't mean
to interrupt things.

256
00:13:52,274 --> 00:13:55,107
He isn't a good swimmer,
and it's a little too soon...

257
00:13:55,144 --> 00:13:56,873
for him to be out here
unsupervised.

258
00:13:56,912 --> 00:13:58,675
I can assure you,
he's quite safe with me.

259
00:13:58,714 --> 00:14:01,683
I'm sure he is,
but you have a large class...

260
00:14:01,717 --> 00:14:04,550
and he can get lost from sight
if you're not looking.

261
00:14:04,587 --> 00:14:05,787
I'm not saying
you're not looking.

262
00:14:05,821 --> 00:14:08,756
Oh, my gosh!
Nemo's swimming out to sea!

263
00:14:10,559 --> 00:14:11,821
Nemo!

264
00:14:13,229 --> 00:14:14,924
What do you think you're doing?

265
00:14:14,964 --> 00:14:17,762
You'll get stuck out there...

266
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:21,292
and I'll have to get you
before another fish does.

267
00:14:21,403 --> 00:14:23,234
Get back here!

268
00:14:23,272 --> 00:14:26,264
I said get back here now!

269
00:14:26,308 --> 00:14:31,143
Stop! You take
one more move, mister...

270
00:14:31,180 --> 00:14:33,045
Don't you dare!

271
00:14:33,082 --> 00:14:35,141
If you put one fin
on that boat...

272
00:14:35,184 --> 00:14:36,674
Are you listening to me?

273
00:14:36,719 --> 00:14:40,348
Don't touch the bo... Nemo!

274
00:14:40,389 --> 00:14:42,016
He touched the butt.

275
00:14:42,057 --> 00:14:44,787
You paddle your little tail
right back here, Nemo.

276
00:14:44,827 --> 00:14:45,987
That's right.

277
00:14:46,028 --> 00:14:47,723
You are in big trouble,
young man.

278
00:14:47,763 --> 00:14:49,560
Do you hear me? Big...

279
00:14:51,367 --> 00:14:53,335
Big...

280
00:14:56,572 --> 00:14:58,631
Daddy! Help me!

281
00:14:58,674 --> 00:15:01,643
I'm coming, Nemo!

282
00:15:02,945 --> 00:15:04,879
Get under me, kids!

283
00:15:04,914 --> 00:15:06,313
Oh! No!

284
00:15:06,348 --> 00:15:08,043
Dad!

285
00:15:08,083 --> 00:15:10,483
Daddy!

286
00:15:13,722 --> 00:15:16,589
Oh! Nemo!

287
00:15:19,028 --> 00:15:21,019
Nemo!

288
00:15:21,063 --> 00:15:24,692
Nemo, no! Nemo!

289
00:15:24,733 --> 00:15:27,702
Nemo! Nemo! No!

290
00:15:29,605 --> 00:15:32,096
No!

291
00:15:41,050 --> 00:15:42,540
Nemo! Nemo!

292
00:15:52,795 --> 00:15:54,057
Hold on.

293
00:16:06,842 --> 00:16:08,070
Oh, no.

294
00:16:08,110 --> 00:16:10,704
No. No, it's gone. It's gone.

295
00:16:10,746 --> 00:16:12,043
No, no, it can't be gone.

296
00:16:12,081 --> 00:16:14,413
No, no! Nemo!

297
00:16:14,450 --> 00:16:16,050
Nemo! Nemo!

298
00:16:16,051 --> 00:16:17,643
Nemo! Nemo!

299
00:16:17,686 --> 00:16:19,916
No!

300
00:16:20,022 --> 00:16:22,616
Nemo! Nemo!

301
00:16:22,658 --> 00:16:25,456
No! No, please, no!

302
00:16:28,264 --> 00:16:29,458
No, no!

303
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:33,391
Has anybody seen a boat?

304
00:16:33,435 --> 00:16:35,266
Please! A white boat!

305
00:16:35,304 --> 00:16:36,965
They took my son!

306
00:16:37,006 --> 00:16:39,507
My son! Help me, please.

307
00:16:39,508 --> 00:16:41,408
- Look out!
- What?

308
00:16:43,879 --> 00:16:47,474
Oh, oh. Sorry.
I didn't see you.

309
00:16:47,516 --> 00:16:50,815
- Sir? Are you OK?
- He's gone, he's gone.

310
00:16:50,853 --> 00:16:52,286
There, there. It's all right.

311
00:16:52,321 --> 00:16:53,583
- He's gone.
- It'll be OK.

312
00:16:53,622 --> 00:16:57,183
No, no. They took him away.
I have to find the boat.

313
00:16:57,226 --> 00:16:59,285
A boat? Hey, I've seen a boat.

314
00:16:59,328 --> 00:17:01,626
- You have?
- It passed by not too long ago.

315
00:17:01,664 --> 00:17:04,030
- A white one?
- Hi. I'm Dory.

316
00:17:04,066 --> 00:17:05,260
Where? Which way?

317
00:17:05,301 --> 00:17:07,462
It went this way.

318
00:17:07,503 --> 00:17:08,902
It went this way. Follow me.

319
00:17:08,938 --> 00:17:12,305
Thank you. Thank you,
thank you so much.

320
00:17:12,341 --> 00:17:13,467
No problem.

321
00:17:38,467 --> 00:17:40,059
Hey...

322
00:17:40,102 --> 00:17:41,501
Wait!

323
00:17:47,609 --> 00:17:49,702
- Will you quit it?
- What?

324
00:17:49,745 --> 00:17:52,509
I'm trying to swim here.
Ocean isn't big enough for you?

325
00:17:52,881 --> 00:17:54,746
You got a problem, buddy?

326
00:17:54,783 --> 00:17:57,479
Do you? Do you?
You want a piece of me?

327
00:17:57,519 --> 00:17:59,384
I'm scared now. What?

328
00:17:59,421 --> 00:18:02,015
- Wait a minute.
- Stop following me, OK?

329
00:18:02,057 --> 00:18:05,185
What? You're showing me
where the boat went.

330
00:18:05,227 --> 00:18:06,829
A boat? Hey, I've seen a boat.

331
00:18:07,062 --> 00:18:10,259
It passed by not too long ago.
It went this way.

332
00:18:10,299 --> 00:18:11,698
It went this way. Follow me.

333
00:18:11,734 --> 00:18:13,861
Wait a minute.
What is going on?

334
00:18:13,902 --> 00:18:16,200
You already told me
which way the boat was going.

335
00:18:16,238 --> 00:18:19,435
I did? Oh, no.

336
00:18:19,475 --> 00:18:21,773
If this is some kind of
practical joke, it's not funny.

337
00:18:21,810 --> 00:18:24,108
And I know funny.
I'm a clownfish.

338
00:18:24,146 --> 00:18:27,547
No, it's not. I know it's not.
I'm so sorry.

339
00:18:27,583 --> 00:18:30,552
See, I suffer from
short-term memory loss.

340
00:18:30,586 --> 00:18:34,420
Short-term memory loss.
I don't believe this.

341
00:18:34,456 --> 00:18:36,321
No, it's true. I forget things
almost instantly.

342
00:18:36,358 --> 00:18:40,317
It runs in my family.
At least, I think it does.

343
00:18:40,362 --> 00:18:44,389
Where are they?

344
00:18:49,138 --> 00:18:50,571
Can I help you?

345
00:18:50,572 --> 00:18:53,234
Something's wrong
with you... really.

346
00:18:53,275 --> 00:18:55,140
You're wasting my time.

347
00:18:55,177 --> 00:18:57,236
I have to find my son.

348
00:19:00,516 --> 00:19:02,040
Hello.

349
00:19:02,084 --> 00:19:04,075
Well, hi!

350
00:19:04,119 --> 00:19:07,145
Name's Bruce.

351
00:19:07,189 --> 00:19:08,952
It's all right. I understand.

352
00:19:08,991 --> 00:19:12,722
Why trust a shark, right?

353
00:19:19,802 --> 00:19:22,896
So, what's a couple
of bites like you...

354
00:19:22,938 --> 00:19:24,599
doing out so late, eh?

355
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:26,665
We're not doing anything.
We're not even out.

356
00:19:26,708 --> 00:19:28,938
Great!
Then how'd you morsels...

357
00:19:28,977 --> 00:19:32,242
like to come to a little
get-together I'm having?

358
00:19:32,281 --> 00:19:33,475
You mean, like a party?

359
00:19:33,515 --> 00:19:37,576
Yeah, right. A party.
What do you say?

360
00:19:37,619 --> 00:19:39,780
I love parties.
That sounds like fun.

361
00:19:39,822 --> 00:19:42,222
Parties are fun,
and it's tempting, but...

362
00:19:42,257 --> 00:19:46,159
Oh, come on, I insist.

363
00:19:46,195 --> 00:19:49,392
OK. That's all that matters.

364
00:19:52,034 --> 00:19:54,195
Hey, look, balloons.
It is a party.

365
00:19:54,236 --> 00:19:56,568
Mind your distance, though.

366
00:19:56,605 --> 00:19:59,267
Those balloons
can be a bit dodgy.

367
00:19:59,308 --> 00:20:01,606
You wouldn't want
one of them to pop.

368
00:20:15,557 --> 00:20:18,185
Anchor! Chum!

369
00:20:18,227 --> 00:20:21,025
There you are, Bruce. Finally.

370
00:20:21,063 --> 00:20:23,725
- We got company.
- It's about time, mate.

371
00:20:23,765 --> 00:20:25,233
We've already gone
through the snacks...

372
00:20:25,267 --> 00:20:26,825
and I'm still starving.

373
00:20:26,869 --> 00:20:29,064
We almost had a feeding frenzy.

374
00:20:29,104 --> 00:20:30,833
Come on,
let's get this over with.

375
00:20:32,074 --> 00:20:33,666
Right, then.

376
00:20:33,709 --> 00:20:36,007
The meeting has officially
come to order.

377
00:20:36,044 --> 00:20:37,534
Let us all say the pledge.

378
00:20:37,579 --> 00:20:42,073
I am a nice shark,
not a mindless eating machine.

379
00:20:42,117 --> 00:20:44,745
If I am to change this image...

380
00:20:44,786 --> 00:20:47,220
I must first change myself.

381
00:20:47,256 --> 00:20:49,986
Fish are friends, not food.

382
00:20:50,025 --> 00:20:51,356
Except stinkin' dolphins.

383
00:20:51,393 --> 00:20:54,419
Dolphins. Yeah.
They think they're so cute.

384
00:20:54,463 --> 00:20:56,192
"Look at me.
I'm a flippin' little dolphin."

385
00:20:56,231 --> 00:20:57,892
"Let me flip for you.
Ain't I something?"

386
00:20:57,933 --> 00:21:00,527
Right, then.
Today's meeting is Step 5...

387
00:21:00,569 --> 00:21:02,230
Bring a Fish Friend.

388
00:21:02,271 --> 00:21:03,761
Do you all have your friends?

389
00:21:03,805 --> 00:21:04,965
Got mine.

390
00:21:06,875 --> 00:21:08,968
- Hey, there.
- How about you, Chum?

391
00:21:09,011 --> 00:21:13,539
Oh, I... seem to have
misplaced my friend.

392
00:21:15,150 --> 00:21:16,515
That's all right, Chum.

393
00:21:16,552 --> 00:21:18,076
I had a feeling
this would be a difficult step.

394
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:19,644
You can help yourself
to one of my friends.

395
00:21:19,688 --> 00:21:23,146
Thanks, mate.
A little chum for Chum?

396
00:21:23,192 --> 00:21:24,853
I'll start the testimonies.

397
00:21:24,893 --> 00:21:27,123
Hello. My name is Bruce.

398
00:21:27,162 --> 00:21:28,424
Hello, Bruce.

399
00:21:28,463 --> 00:21:30,624
It has been three weeks
since my last fish.

400
00:21:30,666 --> 00:21:34,102
On my honor, or may I be
chopped up and made into soup.

401
00:21:34,136 --> 00:21:36,900
- You're an inspiration!
- Amen.

402
00:21:38,140 --> 00:21:39,573
Right, then. Who's next?

403
00:21:39,608 --> 00:21:40,905
Pick me, pick me.

404
00:21:40,943 --> 00:21:42,808
Yes. The little
Sheila down the front.

405
00:21:42,844 --> 00:21:44,903
Come on up here.

406
00:21:45,881 --> 00:21:47,746
Hi. I'm Dory.

407
00:21:47,783 --> 00:21:50,183
- Hello, Dory.
- And well...

408
00:21:50,219 --> 00:21:53,382
I don't think
I've ever eaten a fish.

409
00:21:53,422 --> 00:21:56,983
- That's incredible.
- Good on you, mate.

410
00:21:57,025 --> 00:21:59,050
I'm glad
I got that off my chest.

411
00:21:59,094 --> 00:22:00,425
All right, anyone else?

412
00:22:00,462 --> 00:22:03,056
How about you, mate?
What's your problem?

413
00:22:03,098 --> 00:22:05,328
Me? I don't have a problem.

414
00:22:05,367 --> 00:22:06,732
Oh, OK.

415
00:22:06,768 --> 00:22:08,360
Denial.

416
00:22:08,403 --> 00:22:10,234
Just start with your name.

417
00:22:10,272 --> 00:22:12,968
OK. Hello.

418
00:22:13,008 --> 00:22:16,102
My name is Marlin.
I'm a clownfish.

419
00:22:16,144 --> 00:22:19,170
- A clownfish? Really?
- Tell us a joke.

420
00:22:19,214 --> 00:22:20,943
I love jokes.

421
00:22:20,983 --> 00:22:23,975
I actually do know one
that's pretty good.

422
00:22:24,019 --> 00:22:26,044
There was this mollusk...

423
00:22:26,088 --> 00:22:28,420
and he walks up
to a sea cucumber.

424
00:22:28,457 --> 00:22:30,288
Normally, they don't talk,
sea cucumbers...

425
00:22:30,325 --> 00:22:32,293
but in a joke,
everyone talks...

426
00:22:32,327 --> 00:22:35,387
so the sea mollusk
says to the cucumber...

427
00:22:37,099 --> 00:22:39,693
Daddy!

428
00:22:39,735 --> 00:22:41,066
Nemo!

429
00:22:41,103 --> 00:22:44,129
Nemo! Nemo! I don't get it.

430
00:22:44,172 --> 00:22:46,072
For a clownfish,
he's not that funny.

431
00:22:46,108 --> 00:22:47,939
No, no, no, no. He's my son.

432
00:22:47,976 --> 00:22:50,035
He was taken by these divers.

433
00:22:50,078 --> 00:22:52,774
Oh, my. You poor fish.

434
00:22:52,814 --> 00:22:54,782
Humans... think they own
everything.

435
00:22:54,816 --> 00:22:56,078
Probably American.

436
00:22:56,118 --> 00:23:00,219
Now, there is a father...
Looking for his little boy.

437
00:23:00,289 --> 00:23:02,780
What do these markings mean?

438
00:23:02,824 --> 00:23:05,156
I never knew my father!

439
00:23:05,193 --> 00:23:07,593
- Group hug.
- We're all mates here, mate.

440
00:23:07,629 --> 00:23:08,857
I can't read human.

441
00:23:08,897 --> 00:23:10,159
We got to find a fish
that can read this.

442
00:23:10,198 --> 00:23:12,166
- Hey, look, sharks.
- No, no, no, Dory!

443
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:14,327
- Guys, guys.
- No, Dory.

444
00:23:14,369 --> 00:23:15,700
That's mine. Give it to me.

445
00:23:15,737 --> 00:23:17,204
Gimme!

446
00:23:17,239 --> 00:23:19,207
Oh, I'm sorry. Are you OK?

447
00:23:19,308 --> 00:23:20,639
I'm so sorry.

448
00:23:20,676 --> 00:23:22,803
You really clocked me there.
Am I bleeding?

449
00:23:24,780 --> 00:23:28,341
Dory, are you OK...

450
00:23:28,383 --> 00:23:29,184
That's good.

451
00:23:29,185 --> 00:23:31,914
That's good.

452
00:23:31,953 --> 00:23:33,853
Intervention!

453
00:23:33,889 --> 00:23:36,483
- Just a bite.
- Hold it together, mate!

454
00:23:36,525 --> 00:23:39,153
Remember, Bruce,
fish are friends, not food!

455
00:23:39,194 --> 00:23:42,096
- Food!
- Dory, look out!

456
00:23:42,130 --> 00:23:45,691
I'm having fish tonight!

457
00:23:45,734 --> 00:23:47,326
Remember the steps, mate!

458
00:23:53,141 --> 00:23:55,405
Just one bite!

459
00:23:58,480 --> 00:24:02,246
G'day. Grr!

460
00:24:03,285 --> 00:24:04,547
There's no way out!

461
00:24:04,586 --> 00:24:06,349
There's got to be a way
to escape!

462
00:24:08,557 --> 00:24:09,890
Who is it?

463
00:24:09,891 --> 00:24:11,256
Dory, help me find a way out!

464
00:24:11,293 --> 00:24:13,818
Sorry. Come back later.
We're trying to escape.

465
00:24:15,063 --> 00:24:18,430
- There's got to be a way out!
- Here's something.

466
00:24:18,467 --> 00:24:21,197
"Es-cap-e."
I wonder what that means.

467
00:24:21,236 --> 00:24:22,760
Funny. It's spelled
just like "escape."

468
00:24:22,804 --> 00:24:24,066
Let's go.

469
00:24:24,106 --> 00:24:27,200
Here's Brucey!

470
00:24:27,242 --> 00:24:28,937
Wait a minute. You can read?

471
00:24:28,977 --> 00:24:30,968
I can read?
That's right. I can read!

472
00:24:31,012 --> 00:24:33,139
Well, then, here.
Read this now.

473
00:24:35,183 --> 00:24:37,947
He really doesn't mean it.
He never even knew his father.

474
00:24:37,986 --> 00:24:39,214
Don't fall off the wagon!

475
00:24:43,291 --> 00:24:45,727
Oh, no, it's blocked!

476
00:24:49,965 --> 00:24:51,262
No, Bruce, focus.

477
00:24:51,299 --> 00:24:53,426
Sorry about Bruce, mate.

478
00:24:53,468 --> 00:24:56,130
He's really a nice guy.

479
00:24:56,171 --> 00:24:57,399
I need to get that mask.

480
00:24:57,439 --> 00:24:59,031
You want that mask? OK.

481
00:24:59,074 --> 00:25:01,838
No, no, no, no, no, no!

482
00:25:01,877 --> 00:25:04,402
Quick, grab the mask!

483
00:25:08,784 --> 00:25:11,116
Oh, no. Bruce?

484
00:25:11,153 --> 00:25:12,780
What?

485
00:25:14,089 --> 00:25:17,354
Swim away! Swim away!

486
00:25:17,392 --> 00:25:19,121
Aw, is the party over?

487
00:25:28,470 --> 00:25:30,404
Nice.

488
00:25:33,499 --> 00:25:34,659
Dad?

489
00:25:37,503 --> 00:25:38,697
Daddy?

490
00:26:01,560 --> 00:26:03,494
Barbara.

491
00:26:03,529 --> 00:26:05,360
Prep for his anterior crown,
would you, please?

492
00:26:05,398 --> 00:26:07,832
And I'm going to need
a few more cotton rolls.

493
00:26:07,867 --> 00:26:09,494
OK.

494
00:26:11,237 --> 00:26:12,966
Hello, little fella.

495
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:15,400
Beauty, isn't he?

496
00:26:15,441 --> 00:26:16,772
I found that guy
struggling for life...

497
00:26:16,809 --> 00:26:18,504
out on the reef,
and I saved him.

498
00:26:18,544 --> 00:26:20,637
So, has that Novocaine
kicked in yet?

499
00:26:20,680 --> 00:26:23,877
I think so.
We're ready to roll.

500
00:26:25,117 --> 00:26:26,641
Bubbles!

501
00:26:29,622 --> 00:26:31,214
My bubbles.

502
00:26:31,257 --> 00:26:32,622
He likes bubbles.

503
00:26:32,658 --> 00:26:36,355
No!

504
00:26:44,136 --> 00:26:45,364
Bonjour.

505
00:26:45,404 --> 00:26:49,204
Slow down, little fella.
There's nothing to worry about.

506
00:26:49,241 --> 00:26:52,472
- He's scared to death.
- I want to go home.

507
00:26:52,511 --> 00:26:54,536
Do you know where my dad is?

508
00:26:54,580 --> 00:26:57,344
Honey, your dad's probably
back at the pet store.

509
00:26:57,383 --> 00:26:58,543
Pet store?

510
00:26:58,584 --> 00:27:01,280
Yeah, you know, like,
I'm from Bob's Fish Mart.

511
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:02,878
- Pet Palace.
- Fish-O-Rama.

512
00:27:02,922 --> 00:27:04,389
- Mail order.
- Ebay.

513
00:27:04,423 --> 00:27:07,119
- So, which one is it?
- I'm from the ocean.

514
00:27:07,159 --> 00:27:09,093
The ocean. The ocean?

515
00:27:11,063 --> 00:27:13,759
He hasn't been decontaminated.
Jacques!

516
00:27:13,799 --> 00:27:15,130
- Oui.
- Clean him!

517
00:27:15,167 --> 00:27:16,691
Oui.

518
00:27:16,736 --> 00:27:19,170
- Ocean.
- La mer. Bon.

519
00:27:21,006 --> 00:27:23,133
Voila. He is clean.

520
00:27:25,611 --> 00:27:28,876
The big blue. What's it like?

521
00:27:28,914 --> 00:27:32,941
- Big and blue?
- I knew it.

522
00:27:32,985 --> 00:27:36,182
If there's anything you need,
just ask your Auntie Deb.

523
00:27:36,222 --> 00:27:39,316
Or if I'm not around,
you can talk to my sister Flo.

524
00:27:39,358 --> 00:27:41,121
Hi. How are you?

525
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:42,684
Don't listen to anything
my sister says.

526
00:27:42,728 --> 00:27:44,559
She's nuts.

527
00:27:44,597 --> 00:27:45,689
We got a live one.

528
00:27:45,731 --> 00:27:48,757
- Can't hear you, Peach.
- I said we got a live one.

529
00:27:48,801 --> 00:27:50,769
- Boy, oh, boy.
- What do we got?

530
00:27:50,803 --> 00:27:52,327
Root canal... and by the looks
of those x-rays...

531
00:27:52,371 --> 00:27:53,838
it's not going to be pretty.

532
00:27:55,608 --> 00:27:57,041
- Dam and clamp installed?
- Yep.

533
00:27:57,076 --> 00:27:58,873
- What did he use to open?
- Gator-Glidden drill.

534
00:27:58,911 --> 00:28:00,572
He seems to favor
that one lately.

535
00:28:00,613 --> 00:28:03,548
I can't see, Flo.

536
00:28:03,582 --> 00:28:05,709
You're getting a little too...

537
00:28:05,751 --> 00:28:06,945
Now he's doing
the Schilder technique.

538
00:28:06,986 --> 00:28:08,385
He's using a Hedstrom file.

539
00:28:08,421 --> 00:28:10,616
That's not a Hedstrom file.
That's a K-Flex.

540
00:28:10,656 --> 00:28:13,284
It has a teardrop cross-section.
Clearly a Hedstrom.

541
00:28:13,325 --> 00:28:14,815
- No, no, K-Flex.
- Hedstrom.

542
00:28:14,860 --> 00:28:16,555
- K-Flex!
- Hedstrom!

543
00:28:16,595 --> 00:28:18,654
There I go.
A little help, over here.

544
00:28:18,764 --> 00:28:20,561
I'll go deflate him.

545
00:28:23,002 --> 00:28:25,163
All right. Go ahead and rinse.

546
00:28:25,204 --> 00:28:28,537
Oh, the human mouth
is a disgusting place.

547
00:28:30,976 --> 00:28:32,910
- Hey, Nigel.
- What did I miss?

548
00:28:32,945 --> 00:28:34,105
Root canal... a doozy.

549
00:28:34,146 --> 00:28:35,773
Root canal?
What did he use to open?

550
00:28:35,815 --> 00:28:37,840
- Gator-Glidden drill.
- He's favoring that one.

551
00:28:37,883 --> 00:28:40,875
Hope he doesn't get surplus
sealer at the portal terminus.

552
00:28:40,920 --> 00:28:44,014
- Hello. Who's this?
- New guy.

553
00:28:44,056 --> 00:28:45,387
The dentist
took him off the reef.

554
00:28:45,424 --> 00:28:47,790
An outie. From my neck
of the woods, eh?

555
00:28:47,827 --> 00:28:49,317
Sorry if I ever took
a snap at you.

556
00:28:49,361 --> 00:28:50,760
Fish gotta swim,
birds gotta eat.

557
00:28:50,796 --> 00:28:52,491
Hey! No, no, no, no!

558
00:28:52,531 --> 00:28:54,123
They're not your fish.
They're my fish.

559
00:28:54,166 --> 00:28:56,964
Come on, go. Go on, shoo!

560
00:28:58,304 --> 00:28:59,965
Aw, the picture broke.

561
00:29:00,005 --> 00:29:02,064
This here's Darla.
She's my niece.

562
00:29:02,107 --> 00:29:03,574
She's going to be
eight this week.

563
00:29:03,609 --> 00:29:05,076
Hey, little fella.

564
00:29:05,110 --> 00:29:06,873
Say hello to your new mummy.

565
00:29:06,912 --> 00:29:09,380
She'll be here Friday
to pick you up.

566
00:29:09,415 --> 00:29:11,246
You're her present.

567
00:29:11,283 --> 00:29:13,342
It's our little secret.

568
00:29:13,385 --> 00:29:14,909
Well, Mr. Tucker,
while that sets up...

569
00:29:14,954 --> 00:29:16,922
I'm going to see a man
about a wallaby.

570
00:29:18,757 --> 00:29:20,657
Oh, Darla.

571
00:29:20,693 --> 00:29:22,558
What? What's wrong with her?

572
00:29:22,595 --> 00:29:25,291
She wouldn't stop
shaking the bag.

573
00:29:25,331 --> 00:29:29,097
- Poor Chuckles.
- He was her present last year.

574
00:29:29,134 --> 00:29:31,500
Hitched a ride
on the porcelain express.

575
00:29:33,372 --> 00:29:35,567
She's a fish killer.

576
00:29:35,608 --> 00:29:37,872
I can't go with that girl.

577
00:29:37,910 --> 00:29:39,673
I have to get back to my dad.

578
00:29:39,712 --> 00:29:43,614
Daddy! Help me!

579
00:29:43,649 --> 00:29:44,809
Oh, he's stuck.

580
00:29:44,850 --> 00:29:47,045
Nobody touch him.

581
00:29:49,321 --> 00:29:51,289
Nobody touch him.

582
00:29:57,029 --> 00:29:58,462
Can you help me?

583
00:29:58,497 --> 00:30:00,464
No. You got yourself in there.

584
00:30:00,533 --> 00:30:02,194
You can get yourself out.

585
00:30:02,234 --> 00:30:04,498
- Gill...
- I want to see him do it.

586
00:30:04,537 --> 00:30:08,371
Calm down. Alternate wiggling
your fins and your tail.

587
00:30:08,407 --> 00:30:11,205
I can't. I have a bad fin.

588
00:30:11,243 --> 00:30:13,404
Never stopped me.

589
00:30:17,483 --> 00:30:20,043
Just think about
what you need to do.

590
00:30:24,023 --> 00:30:25,547
Come on.

591
00:30:29,762 --> 00:30:30,956
Perfect.

592
00:30:30,996 --> 00:30:32,361
- Yay!
- You did it!

593
00:30:32,398 --> 00:30:34,161
Good squirming.

594
00:30:34,199 --> 00:30:37,794
From the ocean...
just like you, Gill.

595
00:30:37,836 --> 00:30:38,996
Yeah.

596
00:30:39,038 --> 00:30:41,404
I've seen that look before.

597
00:30:41,440 --> 00:30:43,101
What are you thinking about?

598
00:30:43,142 --> 00:30:44,905
I'm thinking...

599
00:30:44,944 --> 00:30:48,505
tonight, we give the kid
a proper reception.

600
00:30:48,547 --> 00:30:50,208
So, kid,
you got a name or what?

601
00:30:50,249 --> 00:30:52,945
Nemo. I'm Nemo.

602
00:30:55,087 --> 00:30:57,555
Nemo. Nemo.

603
00:31:02,761 --> 00:31:04,456
Are you gonna eat that?

604
00:31:16,008 --> 00:31:19,671
Careful with that hammer.

605
00:31:22,181 --> 00:31:24,945
No, no.

606
00:31:24,984 --> 00:31:27,214
What does it say? Dory!

607
00:31:27,252 --> 00:31:28,879
A sea monkey has my money.

608
00:31:28,921 --> 00:31:31,185
Wake up. Get up. Come on.

609
00:31:31,223 --> 00:31:32,190
Come on!

610
00:31:32,224 --> 00:31:34,454
- Yes, I'm a natural blue.
- Get up!

611
00:31:34,493 --> 00:31:37,724
Look out! Sharks eat fish!

612
00:31:59,818 --> 00:32:01,877
Dusty.

613
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,444
The mask. Where's the mask?

614
00:32:05,124 --> 00:32:07,024
No! No, not the mask!

615
00:32:07,059 --> 00:32:09,584
Get it! Get the mask!
Get the mask! Get it!

616
00:32:13,766 --> 00:32:16,257
Hoo doot doo doot doot doo doot

617
00:32:17,736 --> 00:32:19,294
La la la la la la

618
00:32:19,338 --> 00:32:21,067
it just keeps going on,
doesn't it?

619
00:32:21,106 --> 00:32:23,506
Echo! Echo!

620
00:32:23,542 --> 00:32:24,770
Hey, what you doing?

621
00:32:24,810 --> 00:32:26,072
It's gone. I've lost the mask.

622
00:32:26,111 --> 00:32:28,136
- Did you drop it?
- You dropped it!

623
00:32:28,180 --> 00:32:29,772
That was my only chance
of finding my son.

624
00:32:29,815 --> 00:32:32,113
Now it's gone.

625
00:32:34,720 --> 00:32:38,588
Hey, Mr. Grumpy Gills...

626
00:32:38,624 --> 00:32:40,216
when life gets you down,
know what you got to do?

627
00:32:40,259 --> 00:32:42,693
- I don't want to know.
- Just keep swimming.

628
00:32:42,728 --> 00:32:46,164
Just keep swimming,
swimming, swimming

629
00:32:46,198 --> 00:32:48,428
What do we do? We swim, swim

630
00:32:48,467 --> 00:32:49,695
Dory, no singing.

631
00:32:49,735 --> 00:32:51,532
Ho ho ho ho ho ho

632
00:32:51,570 --> 00:32:54,164
I love to swim

633
00:32:54,206 --> 00:32:56,640
When you want to swim

634
00:32:56,675 --> 00:32:58,666
See, I'm going to get
stuck now with that song.

635
00:32:58,711 --> 00:33:02,947
- Now it's in my head.
- Sorry.

636
00:33:02,948 --> 00:33:04,381
Dory, do you see anything?

637
00:33:04,416 --> 00:33:06,145
- Something's got me.
- That was me. I'm sorry.

638
00:33:06,185 --> 00:33:09,552
- Who's that?
- Who could it be? It's me.

639
00:33:09,588 --> 00:33:12,853
Are you my conscience?

640
00:33:12,891 --> 00:33:15,519
Yeah, yeah.
I'm your conscience.

641
00:33:15,561 --> 00:33:18,462
We haven't spoken for a while.
How are you?

642
00:33:18,497 --> 00:33:20,761
- Can't complain.
- Yeah? Good.

643
00:33:20,799 --> 00:33:22,528
Now, Dory,
I want you to tell me...

644
00:33:22,568 --> 00:33:24,297
Do you see anything?

645
00:33:24,336 --> 00:33:27,931
I see a... I see a light.

646
00:33:27,973 --> 00:33:30,533
- A light?
- Yeah. Over there.

647
00:33:30,576 --> 00:33:34,034
- Hey, conscience, am I dead?
- No. I see it, too.

648
00:33:41,720 --> 00:33:43,711
What is it?

649
00:33:43,756 --> 00:33:48,557
It's so pretty.

650
00:33:48,594 --> 00:33:53,395
I'm feeling... happy...

651
00:33:53,432 --> 00:33:56,924
which is a big deal for me.

652
00:33:56,969 --> 00:33:58,459
I want to touch it.

653
00:34:00,072 --> 00:34:02,472
Hey, come back.
Come on back here.

654
00:34:02,508 --> 00:34:04,066
I'm gonna get you

655
00:34:04,109 --> 00:34:05,872
I'm gonna get you.

656
00:34:05,911 --> 00:34:07,173
I'm gonna swim with you

657
00:34:07,212 --> 00:34:08,577
I'm gonna get you.

658
00:34:08,614 --> 00:34:11,481
I'm gonna be your best friend

659
00:34:11,517 --> 00:34:12,677
Good feeling's gone.

660
00:34:19,525 --> 00:34:22,289
I can't see!
I don't know where I'm going!

661
00:34:24,196 --> 00:34:26,164
- The mask!
- What mask?

662
00:34:26,198 --> 00:34:28,496
OK, I can't see a thing.

663
00:34:29,902 --> 00:34:32,200
- Oh, gee.
- Hey, look, a mask.

664
00:34:32,237 --> 00:34:33,898
Read it!

665
00:34:33,939 --> 00:34:35,566
I'm sorry,
but if you could just...

666
00:34:35,607 --> 00:34:37,542
bring it a little closer,
I kind of need the light.

667
00:34:37,576 --> 00:34:40,511
That's great.
Keep it right there.

668
00:34:40,546 --> 00:34:43,276
- Just read it!
- OK, OK.

669
00:34:43,315 --> 00:34:46,341
Mr. Bossy. "P."

670
00:34:46,385 --> 00:34:49,354
OK. "P. Sher..."

671
00:34:49,388 --> 00:34:52,482
"Sher... P. Sher..."
P. Shirley? P..."

672
00:34:54,393 --> 00:34:56,691
Oh. The first line's
"P. Sherman."

673
00:34:56,728 --> 00:34:58,923
"P. Sherman"
doesn't make any sense!

674
00:34:58,964 --> 00:35:01,194
OK. Second line. "42."

675
00:35:01,233 --> 00:35:03,201
Don't eat me. Don't eat me.

676
00:35:04,937 --> 00:35:06,529
Light, please!

677
00:35:07,906 --> 00:35:10,466
"Walla... walla..."

678
00:35:10,509 --> 00:35:13,410
Waah! Waah! Waah!

679
00:35:13,445 --> 00:35:15,208
The second line's
"42 Wallaby Way."

680
00:35:15,247 --> 00:35:18,045
That's great.
Speed read. Take a guess.

681
00:35:18,083 --> 00:35:19,710
No pressure. No problem.
There's a lot of pressure.

682
00:35:19,751 --> 00:35:22,276
Pressure! Take a guess
now with pressure!

683
00:35:22,321 --> 00:35:25,415
- "Sydney"! It's "Sydney"!
- Duck!

684
00:35:27,426 --> 00:35:30,827
I'm dead.
I'm dead, I'm dead, I'm dead.

685
00:35:30,863 --> 00:35:32,228
I died. I'm dead.

686
00:35:40,606 --> 00:35:42,403
We did it, we did it

687
00:35:42,441 --> 00:35:44,136
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah

688
00:35:44,176 --> 00:35:46,007
No eating here tonight, whoo!

689
00:35:46,044 --> 00:35:47,409
Eating here tonight

690
00:35:47,446 --> 00:35:48,743
No, no, no, eating here tonight

691
00:35:48,780 --> 00:35:50,247
- Dory.
- You on a diet

692
00:35:50,282 --> 00:35:53,115
Dory! What did the mask say?

693
00:35:53,151 --> 00:35:54,982
P. Sherman,
42 Wallaby Way, Sydney.

694
00:35:55,020 --> 00:35:57,147
I remembered what it said!

695
00:35:57,189 --> 00:35:59,680
I usually forget things,
but I remembered it!

696
00:35:59,725 --> 00:36:01,386
Wait. Where is that?

697
00:36:01,426 --> 00:36:03,860
I don't know.
But who cares? I remembered.

698
00:36:03,896 --> 00:36:05,090
Raar!

699
00:36:05,130 --> 00:36:07,360
P. Sherman,
42 Wallaby Way, Sydney.

700
00:36:07,399 --> 00:36:09,424
I remembered it again!

701
00:36:36,128 --> 00:36:39,120
Nemo.

702
00:36:40,799 --> 00:36:43,495
Nemo

703
00:36:43,535 --> 00:36:46,402
Suivez-moi.

704
00:36:48,540 --> 00:36:50,132
Follow me.

705
00:37:36,054 --> 00:37:37,646
Hahoo wahoo yahoo ho

706
00:37:37,689 --> 00:37:40,055
Hahoo wahoo yahoo ho

707
00:37:40,092 --> 00:37:42,185
Hahoo ho ho wahoo ha hee

708
00:37:42,227 --> 00:37:44,422
Ha ho wahee ha ho ho ho

709
00:37:44,463 --> 00:37:45,657
Hoo!

710
00:37:47,666 --> 00:37:49,395
State your name.

711
00:37:49,434 --> 00:37:51,527
Nemo.

712
00:37:51,570 --> 00:37:53,902
Brother Bloat, proceed.

713
00:37:55,040 --> 00:37:58,942
Nemo, newcomer
of orange and white...

714
00:37:58,977 --> 00:38:00,342
you have been called forth...

715
00:38:00,379 --> 00:38:02,939
to the summit of
Mount Wannahockaloogie...

716
00:38:02,981 --> 00:38:08,283
to join with us in
the fraternal bonds of tankhood.

717
00:38:08,320 --> 00:38:11,221
We want you in our club, kid.

718
00:38:11,256 --> 00:38:12,450
- Really?
- If...

719
00:38:12,491 --> 00:38:15,756
you are able to swim through...

720
00:38:15,794 --> 00:38:20,254
the Ring of Fire!

721
00:38:23,769 --> 00:38:25,600
Turn on the Ring of Fire!

722
00:38:25,637 --> 00:38:27,264
You said you could do it.

723
00:38:27,305 --> 00:38:28,897
The Ring of Fire!

724
00:38:31,276 --> 00:38:33,403
Bubbles, let me... Oh!

725
00:38:33,445 --> 00:38:36,209
Ha hwa ha ho ho ho

726
00:38:36,248 --> 00:38:38,580
Ha hwa ha ho ho ho

727
00:38:38,617 --> 00:38:40,949
Ha hwa ha ho ho ho

728
00:38:40,986 --> 00:38:44,080
Isn't there another way?
He's just a boy!

729
00:38:54,466 --> 00:38:59,563
From this moment on,
you will be known as Sharkbait.

730
00:38:59,604 --> 00:39:00,935
Sharkbait, oo-ha-ha!

731
00:39:00,972 --> 00:39:02,735
Welcome, Brother Sharkbait.

732
00:39:02,774 --> 00:39:04,002
Sharkbait, oo-ha-ha!

733
00:39:04,042 --> 00:39:06,067
- Enough with the Sharkbait.
- Sharkbait!

734
00:39:06,111 --> 00:39:07,976
Ba-ba-do.

735
00:39:08,013 --> 00:39:09,571
Sharkbait's
one of us now, agreed?

736
00:39:09,614 --> 00:39:11,673
- Agreed.
- We can't send him to his death.

737
00:39:11,716 --> 00:39:13,809
Darla's coming in five days.

738
00:39:13,852 --> 00:39:15,410
So, what are we going to do?

739
00:39:15,454 --> 00:39:18,014
I'll tell you
what we're gonna do...

740
00:39:18,056 --> 00:39:19,614
we're gonna get him
out of here.

741
00:39:19,658 --> 00:39:22,183
- We'll help him escape.
- Escape? Really?

742
00:39:22,227 --> 00:39:23,694
We're all gonna escape.

743
00:39:23,728 --> 00:39:26,356
Gill, please.
Not another escape plan.

744
00:39:26,398 --> 00:39:28,423
Sorry,
but they just never work.

745
00:39:28,467 --> 00:39:30,001
Why should this
be any different?

746
00:39:30,035 --> 00:39:33,493
- Because we've got him.
- Me?

747
00:39:33,538 --> 00:39:35,306
- You see that filter?
- Yeah.

748
00:39:35,307 --> 00:39:38,743
You're the only one who can get
in and out of that thing.

749
00:39:38,777 --> 00:39:41,940
We need you to take
a pebble inside there...

750
00:39:41,980 --> 00:39:43,208
and jam the gears.

751
00:39:43,248 --> 00:39:45,216
You do that,
and this tank's gonna get...

752
00:39:45,250 --> 00:39:47,218
filthier and filthier
by the minute.

753
00:39:47,252 --> 00:39:49,584
Pretty soon, the dentist'll
have to clean the tank...

754
00:39:49,621 --> 00:39:52,522
and when he does, he'll take us
out of the tank...

755
00:39:52,557 --> 00:39:54,115
put us in individual baggies...

756
00:39:54,159 --> 00:39:55,956
then we'll roll ourselves
down the counter...

757
00:39:55,994 --> 00:39:57,655
out the window,
off the awning...

758
00:39:57,696 --> 00:39:59,357
into the bushes,
across the street...

759
00:39:59,397 --> 00:40:01,865
and into the harbor!

760
00:40:01,900 --> 00:40:04,835
It's foolproof. Who's with me?

761
00:40:04,870 --> 00:40:06,269
- Aye!
- Aye!

762
00:40:06,304 --> 00:40:07,737
I think you're nuts.

763
00:40:08,907 --> 00:40:11,740
No offense, kid,
but you're not the best swimmer.

764
00:40:11,776 --> 00:40:14,176
He's fine. He can do this.

765
00:40:14,212 --> 00:40:17,670
So, Sharkbait,
what do you think?

766
00:40:17,716 --> 00:40:22,653
Let's do it.

767
00:40:22,654 --> 00:40:25,623
I'm going to P. Sherman,
42 Wallaby Way, Sydney.

768
00:40:25,657 --> 00:40:26,954
Where are you going?

769
00:40:26,992 --> 00:40:28,653
I'm going to P. Sherman,
42 Wallaby Way, Sydney.

770
00:40:28,693 --> 00:40:30,320
If you ask where I'm going...

771
00:40:30,362 --> 00:40:32,091
I'll tell you
that's where I'm going.

772
00:40:32,130 --> 00:40:33,597
It's P. Sherman,
42 Wallaby Way, Sydney.

773
00:40:33,632 --> 00:40:35,395
Where? I'm sorry,
I didn't hear you.

774
00:40:35,433 --> 00:40:36,991
P. Sherman,
42 Wallaby Way, Sydney.

775
00:40:37,035 --> 00:40:39,833
Excuse me.

776
00:40:39,871 --> 00:40:41,668
Hi. Do you know how to get...

777
00:40:41,706 --> 00:40:44,675
Hello? Wait. Can you tell me...

778
00:40:44,709 --> 00:40:49,043
Hey! Hold it!
I'm trying to talk to you!

779
00:40:49,080 --> 00:40:52,447
Fellas, come back here.
One quick question.

780
00:40:52,484 --> 00:40:56,887
I need to...
And they're gone again.

781
00:40:56,922 --> 00:40:58,685
P. Sherman,
42 Wallaby Way, Sydney.

782
00:40:58,723 --> 00:41:00,384
Why do I have to tell you
over and over again?

783
00:41:00,425 --> 00:41:02,416
I'll tell you again.
I don't get tired of it...

784
00:41:02,460 --> 00:41:03,620
OK, all right.

785
00:41:03,662 --> 00:41:05,357
Here's the thing.

786
00:41:05,397 --> 00:41:10,892
I think it's best
if I carry on from here by...

787
00:41:10,936 --> 00:41:12,301
by myself.

788
00:41:12,337 --> 00:41:13,531
OK.

789
00:41:13,572 --> 00:41:15,267
You know, alone.

790
00:41:15,307 --> 00:41:17,332
Without... without...
I mean, not without you.

791
00:41:17,375 --> 00:41:20,742
But I don't
want you... with me.

792
00:41:20,779 --> 00:41:23,111
Am I...

793
00:41:23,148 --> 00:41:24,308
I don't want to hurt
your feelings.

794
00:41:24,349 --> 00:41:27,147
- You want me to leave?
- I mean, not... Yes.

795
00:41:27,185 --> 00:41:29,619
I just can't afford
any more delays...

796
00:41:29,654 --> 00:41:32,851
and you're one of those fish
that cause delays.

797
00:41:32,891 --> 00:41:34,518
Sometimes it's a good thing.

798
00:41:34,559 --> 00:41:37,585
There's a whole group of fish.
They're delay fish.

799
00:41:37,629 --> 00:41:39,187
You mean...

800
00:41:39,231 --> 00:41:40,892
You mean you don't like me?

801
00:41:40,932 --> 00:41:42,729
No, of course I like you.

802
00:41:42,767 --> 00:41:45,463
It's because I like you
I don't want to be with you.

803
00:41:45,503 --> 00:41:47,664
It's a complicated emotion.

804
00:41:47,706 --> 00:41:51,403
Don't cry. I like you.

805
00:41:51,443 --> 00:41:55,812
Hey, you!
Lady, is this guy bothering you?

806
00:41:55,847 --> 00:41:57,781
I don't remember. Were you?

807
00:41:57,816 --> 00:41:59,716
No, no, no, no, no.
We're just...

808
00:41:59,751 --> 00:42:01,514
Do you guys know
how I can get to...

809
00:42:01,553 --> 00:42:03,885
Look, pal, we're talking
to the lady, not you.

810
00:42:03,922 --> 00:42:05,514
Hey, hey. You like impressions?

811
00:42:07,626 --> 00:42:09,958
Just like in rehearsals,
gentlemen.

812
00:42:09,995 --> 00:42:11,553
So what are we? Take a guess.

813
00:42:11,596 --> 00:42:12,893
I've seen one of those.

814
00:42:12,931 --> 00:42:15,126
I'm a fish with a nose
like a sword.

815
00:42:15,166 --> 00:42:17,134
- Wait, wait...
- It's a swordfish!

816
00:42:17,168 --> 00:42:20,237
Hey, clown boy,
let the lady guess.

817
00:42:20,238 --> 00:42:21,796
Where's the butter?

818
00:42:21,840 --> 00:42:23,239
It's on the tip of my tongue!

819
00:42:23,275 --> 00:42:25,266
- Lobster.
- Saw that!

820
00:42:25,310 --> 00:42:27,141
Lots of legs!
Live in the ocean.

821
00:42:27,178 --> 00:42:28,577
- Clam!
- Close enough!

822
00:42:28,613 --> 00:42:30,103
Oh, it's a whale of a tale

823
00:42:30,148 --> 00:42:31,615
I'll tell you, lad...

824
00:42:31,650 --> 00:42:32,639
They're good.

825
00:42:32,684 --> 00:42:33,981
Will somebody please
give me directions?!

826
00:42:34,019 --> 00:42:36,385
"Will somebody please
give me directions?!"

827
00:42:36,421 --> 00:42:38,446
I'm serious!

828
00:42:38,490 --> 00:42:40,481
"Blah blah blah, me, me, blah!"

829
00:42:40,525 --> 00:42:41,719
"Blah blah blah, me, me, me!"

830
00:42:41,760 --> 00:42:43,250
Thank you.

831
00:42:43,295 --> 00:42:45,786
Oh, dear. Hey! Hey, come back!

832
00:42:45,830 --> 00:42:48,466
- Hey, what's the matter?
- What's the matter?

833
00:42:48,533 --> 00:42:50,501
While they're doing their
silly little impressions...

834
00:42:50,535 --> 00:42:54,665
I am miles from home with a fish
that can't remember her name!

835
00:42:54,706 --> 00:42:56,003
I bet that's frustrating.

836
00:42:56,041 --> 00:42:57,474
Meanwhile, my son is out there.

837
00:42:57,509 --> 00:42:59,500
- Your son Chico?
- Nemo?

838
00:42:59,544 --> 00:43:00,943
But it doesn't matter
because no fish...

839
00:43:00,979 --> 00:43:02,947
in this entire ocean
is going to help me.

840
00:43:02,981 --> 00:43:06,747
Well, I'm helping you.

841
00:43:06,785 --> 00:43:08,116
Wait right here.

842
00:43:09,354 --> 00:43:11,948
- Guys!
- Is he bothering you again?

843
00:43:11,990 --> 00:43:13,514
No, no. He's a good guy.

844
00:43:13,558 --> 00:43:15,759
Go easy on him.
He's lost his son Fabio.

845
00:43:15,827 --> 00:43:18,694
Any of you heard of P. Sherman,
42 Wallaby Way, Sydney?

846
00:43:18,797 --> 00:43:21,425
Sydney? Oh, sure!

847
00:43:21,466 --> 00:43:23,195
Ted here's got relatives
in Sydney.

848
00:43:23,234 --> 00:43:24,861
- Don't you, Ted?
- Sure do!

849
00:43:24,903 --> 00:43:26,393
Oh! Hey! They know Sydney!

850
00:43:27,639 --> 00:43:29,129
You wouldn't know how
to get there, would you?

851
00:43:29,174 --> 00:43:31,142
You want to follow the E.A.C.

852
00:43:31,176 --> 00:43:33,872
That's the East
Australian Current.

853
00:43:33,912 --> 00:43:35,539
Big current. Can't miss it.

854
00:43:35,580 --> 00:43:38,549
It's in... that direction.

855
00:43:38,583 --> 00:43:40,483
And then you follow that
for about...

856
00:43:40,518 --> 00:43:42,281
I don't know.
What do you guys think?

857
00:43:42,320 --> 00:43:43,480
About three leagues?

858
00:43:43,521 --> 00:43:46,490
That little baby will put you
right past Sydney.

859
00:43:46,524 --> 00:43:48,958
- Ta-da!
- That's great!

860
00:43:48,993 --> 00:43:50,187
Dory, you did it!

861
00:43:50,228 --> 00:43:52,059
Oh, please,
I'm just your little helper.

862
00:43:52,097 --> 00:43:54,429
- Helping along. That's me.
- Fellas, thank you.

863
00:43:54,466 --> 00:43:58,095
Don't mention it!
Just loosen up, OK, buddy?

864
00:43:58,136 --> 00:44:01,128
Oh, you guys.
You really nailed him. Bye.

865
00:44:01,172 --> 00:44:03,003
Oh, hey, ma'am. One more thing.

866
00:44:03,041 --> 00:44:06,602
When you come to this trench,
swim through it, not over it.

867
00:44:06,644 --> 00:44:08,544
Trench...
through it, not over it.

868
00:44:08,580 --> 00:44:11,276
I'll remember. Hey, hey!

869
00:44:12,717 --> 00:44:14,981
Hey, wait up, partner! Hold on!

870
00:44:15,019 --> 00:44:17,749
Wait, wait, wait!
I gotta tell you something.

871
00:44:20,525 --> 00:44:22,823
Nice trench.

872
00:44:24,562 --> 00:44:27,554
Hello!

873
00:44:30,268 --> 00:44:32,896
- OK, let's go.
- No, no. Bad trench.

874
00:44:32,937 --> 00:44:34,598
Come on, we'll swim over
this thing.

875
00:44:34,639 --> 00:44:36,766
Partner.
Little red flag going up.

876
00:44:36,808 --> 00:44:40,437
Something's telling me
to swim through it, not over it.

877
00:44:40,478 --> 00:44:42,105
Are you looking at this thing?

878
00:44:42,147 --> 00:44:43,637
It's got death
written all over it.

879
00:44:43,681 --> 00:44:46,514
I really, really, really
think we should swim through.

880
00:44:46,551 --> 00:44:48,781
And I'm really, really done
talking about this. Over we go.

881
00:44:48,820 --> 00:44:50,788
- Trust me on this.
- Trust you?

882
00:44:50,822 --> 00:44:52,687
Yes, trust.
It's what friends do.

883
00:44:52,724 --> 00:44:54,624
Look! Something shiny!

884
00:44:54,659 --> 00:44:56,422
- Where?
- It just swam over the trench.

885
00:44:56,461 --> 00:45:02,166
- Come on, we'll follow it!
- OK!

886
00:45:02,167 --> 00:45:04,829
Boy, it sure is clear up here.

887
00:45:04,869 --> 00:45:08,327
Exactly. And look at that...
there's the current.

888
00:45:08,373 --> 00:45:10,967
We should be there in no time.

889
00:45:11,009 --> 00:45:12,806
Hey, little guy.

890
00:45:12,844 --> 00:45:14,607
You wanted to go
through the trench.

891
00:45:14,646 --> 00:45:16,671
I shall call him Squishy,
and he shall be mine.

892
00:45:16,714 --> 00:45:18,875
And he shall be my Squishy.
Come here, Squishy.

893
00:45:18,983 --> 00:45:20,416
Come here, little Squishy.

894
00:45:23,488 --> 00:45:26,355
- That's a jellyfish!
- Bad Squishy!

895
00:45:26,391 --> 00:45:28,188
Shoo, shoo! Get away!

896
00:45:28,226 --> 00:45:30,524
- Let me see that.
- Don't touch it.

897
00:45:30,562 --> 00:45:32,894
I won't touch it.
I just want to look.

898
00:45:32,931 --> 00:45:34,956
Hey! How come
it didn't sting you?

899
00:45:34,999 --> 00:45:36,523
It did. It's just that...

900
00:45:36,568 --> 00:45:38,263
Hold still.

901
00:45:38,303 --> 00:45:39,770
I live in this anemone...

902
00:45:39,804 --> 00:45:41,669
and I'm used
to these kind of stings.

903
00:45:42,907 --> 00:45:44,898
It doesn't look bad.
You'll be fine.

904
00:45:44,943 --> 00:45:46,672
But now we know, don't we...

905
00:45:46,711 --> 00:45:48,906
that we don't want
to touch these again.

906
00:45:48,947 --> 00:45:51,973
Let's be thankful this time
it was just a little one.

907
00:45:54,452 --> 00:45:55,714
Don't move.

908
00:45:57,555 --> 00:46:00,456
- This is bad, Dory.
- Hey, watch this!

909
00:46:00,492 --> 00:46:02,153
Boing! Boing!

910
00:46:02,193 --> 00:46:03,421
Dory!

911
00:46:03,461 --> 00:46:05,793
You can't catch me

912
00:46:05,830 --> 00:46:07,297
Don't bounce on the tops!

913
00:46:07,332 --> 00:46:10,460
They will... not sting you!

914
00:46:10,502 --> 00:46:13,164
- The tops don't sting you!
- Two in a row! Beat that!

915
00:46:13,204 --> 00:46:16,139
Dory, listen to me.
I have an idea... a game.

916
00:46:16,174 --> 00:46:17,641
- A game?
- Yes.

917
00:46:17,742 --> 00:46:20,404
- I love games! Pick me!
- Here's the game.

918
00:46:20,445 --> 00:46:23,903
Whoever can hop the fastest
out of these jellyfish wins!

919
00:46:23,948 --> 00:46:25,575
- OK.
- Rules, rules, rules!

920
00:46:25,617 --> 00:46:28,177
You can't touch the tentacles.
Only the tops.

921
00:46:28,219 --> 00:46:30,084
Something about tentacles.
Got it. Go!

922
00:46:30,121 --> 00:46:33,056
Wait! Not something about 'em,
it's all about 'em!

923
00:46:33,091 --> 00:46:34,285
- Whee!
- Wait, Dory!

924
00:46:34,325 --> 00:46:36,426
Gotta go faster
if you want to win!

925
00:46:36,461 --> 00:46:37,621
Dory!

926
00:46:37,662 --> 00:46:39,630
Boing, boing, boing!

927
00:46:39,664 --> 00:46:42,531
Wait a minute! Dory!

928
00:46:42,567 --> 00:46:44,091
Whee!

929
00:46:44,135 --> 00:46:47,400
We're cheating death now.
That's what we're doing.

930
00:46:47,438 --> 00:46:49,099
But we're having fun
at the same time.

931
00:46:49,140 --> 00:46:50,573
I can do this. Just be careful.

932
00:46:50,608 --> 00:46:52,508
Yeah, careful I don't
make you cry when I win!

933
00:46:52,544 --> 00:46:53,704
I don't think so!

934
00:46:57,148 --> 00:46:58,308
Give it up, old man.

935
00:46:58,349 --> 00:47:00,613
You can't fight evolution.
I was built for speed.

936
00:47:00,652 --> 00:47:02,620
The question is, Dory,
are you hungry?

937
00:47:02,654 --> 00:47:03,985
- Hungry?
- Yeah.

938
00:47:04,022 --> 00:47:06,752
'Cause you're about
to eat my bubbles!

939
00:47:06,791 --> 00:47:08,952
Duck to the left! Right there!

940
00:47:11,329 --> 00:47:13,763
The clownfish is the winner!

941
00:47:13,798 --> 00:47:16,858
We did it! Look at us!

942
00:47:16,901 --> 00:47:18,428
Dory?

943
00:47:20,663 --> 00:47:22,062
Oh, no.

944
00:47:23,132 --> 00:47:25,430
Dory! Dory!

945
00:47:25,468 --> 00:47:27,561
Dory!

946
00:47:29,539 --> 00:47:31,769
Dory!

947
00:47:35,945 --> 00:47:38,675
Am I disqualified?

948
00:47:38,714 --> 00:47:40,682
No, you're doing fine!
You're actually winning!

949
00:47:40,716 --> 00:47:43,844
But you gotta stay awake.
Where does P. Sherman live?

950
00:47:43,886 --> 00:47:46,787
P. Sherman...
Wallaby Way, Sydney...

951
00:47:46,823 --> 00:47:48,586
That's it!

952
00:47:49,826 --> 00:47:52,522
- Wallaby Way...
- Stay awake!

953
00:47:52,562 --> 00:47:54,860
Stay awake! Stay awake!

954
00:47:54,897 --> 00:47:58,663
Stay... awake!

955
00:48:01,204 --> 00:48:04,469
- Awake.
- P. Sherman.

956
00:48:04,507 --> 00:48:07,499
- Awake.
- 42 Wallaby Way.

957
00:48:07,543 --> 00:48:11,513
Wake up. Nemo...

958
00:48:26,229 --> 00:48:28,595
You miss your dad,
don't you, Sharkbait?

959
00:48:28,631 --> 00:48:29,999
Yeah.

960
00:48:30,032 --> 00:48:34,025
You're lucky to have someone
out there looking for you.

961
00:48:34,070 --> 00:48:36,231
He's not looking for me.

962
00:48:36,272 --> 00:48:39,639
He's scared of the ocean.

963
00:48:39,675 --> 00:48:41,233
Peach, any movement?

964
00:48:41,310 --> 00:48:44,211
He's had four cups of coffee.
It's gotta be soon.

965
00:48:44,247 --> 00:48:45,771
Keep on him.

966
00:48:48,184 --> 00:48:51,017
My first escape...
landed on dental tools.

967
00:48:51,053 --> 00:48:52,486
I was aiming for the toilet.

968
00:48:52,522 --> 00:48:53,716
Toilet?

969
00:48:53,756 --> 00:48:56,350
All drains
lead to the ocean, kid.

970
00:48:56,392 --> 00:48:59,657
How many times have
you tried to get out?

971
00:48:59,695 --> 00:49:01,287
I've lost count.

972
00:49:01,330 --> 00:49:03,264
Fish aren't meant
to be in a box, kid.

973
00:49:03,299 --> 00:49:04,960
It does things to you.

974
00:49:05,001 --> 00:49:07,128
Bubbles! Bubbles!

975
00:49:07,169 --> 00:49:09,535
Potty break! He grabbed
the "Reader's Digest."

976
00:49:09,572 --> 00:49:12,973
- We have 4.2 minutes!
- That's your cue, Sharkbait.

977
00:49:13,009 --> 00:49:15,307
- You can do it, kid.
- We gotta be quick.

978
00:49:15,545 --> 00:49:17,979
Once you get in, swim to
the bottom of the chamber...

979
00:49:18,014 --> 00:49:19,777
and I'll talk you
through the rest.

980
00:49:19,815 --> 00:49:22,613
- OK.
- It'll be a piece of kelp.

981
00:49:31,060 --> 00:49:32,425
Nicely done!

982
00:49:32,461 --> 00:49:34,190
- Can you hear me?
- Yeah!

983
00:49:34,230 --> 00:49:36,721
Here comes the pebble.

984
00:49:38,000 --> 00:49:39,194
Ptoo.

985
00:49:41,671 --> 00:49:44,469
Now, do you see
a small opening?

986
00:49:45,975 --> 00:49:49,138
Inside it,
you'll see a rotating fan.

987
00:49:49,178 --> 00:49:53,706
Wedge that pebble into the fan
to stop it turning.

988
00:49:58,454 --> 00:50:00,752
- Careful, Sharkbait!
- I can't do it!

989
00:50:00,790 --> 00:50:02,314
Gill, this isn't a good idea.

990
00:50:02,358 --> 00:50:04,121
He'll be fine. Try again!

991
00:50:04,160 --> 00:50:06,856
OK.

992
00:50:06,896 --> 00:50:09,364
That's it, Sharkbait.

993
00:50:09,398 --> 00:50:11,696
Nice and steady.

994
00:50:14,170 --> 00:50:15,728
I got it! I got it!

995
00:50:15,771 --> 00:50:18,501
- He did it!
- That's great, kid!

996
00:50:18,541 --> 00:50:20,736
Now swim up the tube and out.

997
00:50:38,027 --> 00:50:40,757
Oh, no! Gill!

998
00:50:40,796 --> 00:50:41,990
- Sharkbait!
- Oh, my gosh!

999
00:50:42,031 --> 00:50:43,259
Get him outta there!

1000
00:50:43,299 --> 00:50:45,824
- What do we do?
- Oh, no!

1001
00:50:45,868 --> 00:50:47,836
Stay calm, kid.
Just don't panic!

1002
00:50:48,871 --> 00:50:50,270
Help me!

1003
00:50:50,306 --> 00:50:52,672
Sharkbait, grab hold of this!

1004
00:50:56,178 --> 00:50:58,146
- No! No! No!
- Feed me more!

1005
00:50:58,180 --> 00:51:01,115
- That's it!
- Sharkbait! Grab it!

1006
00:51:01,150 --> 00:51:03,846
I got it!

1007
00:51:03,886 --> 00:51:05,683
Pull!

1008
00:51:12,361 --> 00:51:15,057
Gill, don't make him
go back in there.

1009
00:51:16,298 --> 00:51:20,325
No. We're done.

1010
00:51:33,382 --> 00:51:35,077
Dude.

1011
00:51:35,117 --> 00:51:38,177
Dude.

1012
00:51:38,220 --> 00:51:42,714
Focus, dude. Dude.

1013
