and I tried to stop them,
but the boat was too fast.

1106
00:56:29,878 --> 00:56:31,641
So, we swam out in the ocean
to follow them...

1107
00:56:31,680 --> 00:56:34,012
They couldn't stop 'em.
And then Nemo's dad...

1108
00:56:34,049 --> 00:56:36,813
he swims out to the ocean,
and they bump into...

1109
00:56:36,852 --> 00:56:38,149
three ferocious sharks.

1110
00:56:38,187 --> 00:56:40,280
He scares away the sharks
by blowing 'em up!

1111
00:56:40,322 --> 00:56:41,653
Golly, that's amazing.

1112
00:56:41,690 --> 00:56:43,317
And then dives
thousands of feet...

1113
00:56:43,359 --> 00:56:45,088
straight down into the dark.

1114
00:56:45,127 --> 00:56:46,594
It's wicked dark down there.

1115
00:56:46,628 --> 00:56:48,323
You can't see a thing.
How's it going, Bob?

1116
00:56:48,364 --> 00:56:50,025
And the only thing
they can see down there...

1117
00:56:50,065 --> 00:56:51,794
is the light from
this big, horrible creature...

1118
00:56:51,834 --> 00:56:53,802
with razor-sharp teeth.
Nice parry, old man.

1119
00:56:53,836 --> 00:56:55,201
And then he has
to blast his way...

1120
00:56:55,237 --> 00:56:56,864
So, these two little fish
have been...

1121
00:56:56,905 --> 00:57:00,441
searching the ocean for days
on the East Australian Current.

1122
00:57:00,442 --> 00:57:02,774
Which means that he may be
on his way here right now.

1123
00:57:02,811 --> 00:57:04,335
That should put him
in Sydney Harbor...

1124
00:57:04,380 --> 00:57:05,677
In a matter of days.
I mean, it sounds like...

1125
00:57:05,714 --> 00:57:07,705
this guy is gonna
stop at nothing...

1126
00:57:07,750 --> 00:57:10,514
till he finds his son.
I sure hope he makes it.

1127
00:57:10,552 --> 00:57:13,544
That's one dedicated father,
if you ask me.

1128
00:57:19,161 --> 00:57:21,095
Mine! Mine! Mine! Mine! Mine!

1129
00:57:21,130 --> 00:57:26,432
Mine! Mine! Mine!
Mine! Mine! Mine!

1130
00:57:26,468 --> 00:57:28,163
Mine! Mine! Mine!
Mine! Mine! Mine!

1131
00:57:28,203 --> 00:57:31,604
Would you just shut up?!

1132
00:57:31,640 --> 00:57:33,107
You're rats with wings!

1133
00:57:33,142 --> 00:57:34,632
Bloke's been looking
for his boy Nemo.

1134
00:57:34,676 --> 00:57:37,008
- Nemo?!
- He was taken off the reef...

1135
00:57:37,046 --> 00:57:40,072
- Take it! You happy?
- Mine! Mine! Mine!

1136
00:57:40,115 --> 00:57:42,913
Hey, say that again!
Something about Nemo.

1137
00:57:42,951 --> 00:57:44,111
Mine! Mine! Mine!

1138
00:57:44,153 --> 00:57:45,643
Whoooa...

1139
00:57:46,889 --> 00:57:48,447
Mine?

1140
00:57:48,490 --> 00:57:50,720
Last I heard, he's heading
towards the harbor.

1141
00:57:50,759 --> 00:57:53,193
Brilliant!

1142
00:58:06,075 --> 00:58:08,076
Is he doing OK?

1143
00:58:08,143 --> 00:58:11,340
Whatever you do,
Don't mention D-a-r...

1144
