will have to clean it.

1212
01:01:15,664 --> 01:01:17,757
Good work!

1213
01:01:24,306 --> 01:01:26,831
All right, we're here, dudes!

1214
01:01:26,875 --> 01:01:30,072
Get ready!
Your exit's coming up, man!

1215
01:01:30,112 --> 01:01:31,602
Where? I don't see it!

1216
01:01:31,647 --> 01:01:34,081
Right there!
I see it! I see it!

1217
01:01:34,116 --> 01:01:37,244
The swirling vortex of terror?

1218
01:01:37,286 --> 01:01:39,584
- That's it, dude.
- Of course it is.

1219
01:01:39,621 --> 01:01:43,648
OK, first,
find your exit buddy.

1220
01:01:43,692 --> 01:01:46,183
Do you have your exit buddy?

1221
01:01:46,228 --> 01:01:47,456
Yes!

1222
01:01:47,496 --> 01:01:52,229
Squirt give you a rundown
of proper exiting technique.

1223
01:01:52,267 --> 01:01:55,794
Good afternoon!
We'll have a great jump today!

1224
01:01:55,837 --> 01:01:59,534
OK, crank a hard cutback
as you hit the wall.

1225
01:01:59,574 --> 01:02:02,509
There's a screaming bottom turn,
so watch out!

1226
01:02:02,544 --> 01:02:05,809
Remember...
rip it, roll it, and punch it!

1227
01:02:05,847 --> 01:02:08,975
He's trying to speak to me,
I know it!

1228
01:02:09,017 --> 01:02:12,248
You're really cute, but I don't
know what you're saying!

1229
01:02:12,287 --> 01:02:13,549
Say the first thing again.

1230
01:02:13,588 --> 01:02:16,113
OK, Jellyman! Go, go, go!

1231
01:02:30,472 --> 01:02:33,066
That was... fun!

1232
01:02:33,108 --> 01:02:35,372
I actually enjoyed that.

1233
01:02:35,410 --> 01:02:37,037
Hey, look, turtles!

1234
01:02:37,079 --> 01:02:40,014
Most excellent!

1235
01:02:40,048 --> 01:02:41,811
Now turn your
fishy tails around...

1236
01:02:41,850 --> 01:02:45,047
and swim straight on
through to Sydney!

1237
01:02:45,087 --> 01:02:47,248
No worries, man!

1238
01:02:47,289 --> 01:02:49,348
No worries!
Thank you, dude Crush!

1239
01:02:49,391 --> 01:02:51,951
- Bye!
- Bye, Jellyman!

1240
01:02:51,993 --> 01:02:54,291
You tell your little dude
I said hi, OK?

1241
01:02:54,329 --> 01:02:55,489
See ya later, dudes!

1242
01:02:55,530 --> 01:02:57,259
Bye, everyone!

1243
01:02:57,299 --> 01:02:59,631
Nemo would have loved this.

1244
01:02:59,668 --> 01:03:03,001
Hey! Crush, I forgot!

1245
01:03:03,038 --> 01:03:04,596
How old are you?

1246
01:03:04,639 --> 01:03:08,837
150, dude!
And still young! Rock on!

1247
01:03:08,877 --> 01:03:12,904
150! 150!
I gotta remember that.

1248
01:03:18,954 --> 01:03:21,582
- We going in there?
- Yep.

1249
01:03:21,623 --> 01:03:23,682
P. Sherman,
42 Wallaby Way, Sydney?

1250
01:03:23,725 --> 01:03:29,357
Yep. We're gonna
just swim straight.

1251
01:03:29,398 --> 01:03:32,162
Just keep swimming,
just keep swimming

1252
01:03:32,200 --> 01:03:33,360
Dory...

1253
01:03:42,144 --> 01:03:44,772
Boy, this is taking awhile.

1254
01:03:44,813 --> 01:03:46,508
How about we play a game?

1255
01:03:46,548 --> 01:03:47,810
OK.

1256
01:03:47,849 --> 01:03:50,909
OK, I'm thinking
of something orange...

1257
01:03:50,952 --> 01:03:52,442
and it's small...

1258
01:03:52,487 --> 01:03:54,785
- It's me.
- Right!

1259
01:03:54,823 --> 01:03:58,384
It's orange and small...

1260
01:03:58,427 --> 01:03:59,724
It's me.

1261
01:03:59,761 --> 01:04:01,661
All righty, Mr. Smartypants.

1262
01:04:01,696 --> 01:04:04,864
And it's orange and small
and white stripes...

1263
01:04:04,900 --> 01:04:07,130
Me. And the next one,
just a guess, me.

1264
01:04:07,169 --> 01:04:09,694
- That's just scary.
- Wait, wait, wait.

1265
01:04:09,738 --> 01:04:11,569
I have definitely seen
this floating speck before.

1266
01:04:11,606 --> 01:04:13,130
That means
we've passed it before...

1267
01:04:13,175 --> 01:04:14,540
and that means
we're going in circles...

1268
01:04:14,576 --> 01:04:16,134
and that means
we're not going straight!

1269
01:04:16,244 --> 01:04:18,337
- Hey, hey!
- Get to the surface.

1270
01:04:18,380 --> 01:04:19,972
We'll figure it out
up there. Let's go!

1271
01:04:20,015 --> 01:04:22,210
- Hey! Relax.
- What?

1272
01:04:22,250 --> 01:04:24,844
Take a deep breath.

1273
01:04:26,788 --> 01:04:29,089
Now, let's ask somebody
for directions.

1274
01:04:29,124 --> 01:04:31,149
Fine. Who do you
want to ask, the speck?

1275
01:04:31,193 --> 01:04:33,559
- There's nobody here!
- There has to be someone.

1276
01:04:33,595 --> 01:04:36,462
It's the ocean, silly.
We're not the only two in here.

1277
01:04:36,498 --> 01:04:38,830
Let's see. OK, no one there.

1278
01:04:38,867 --> 01:04:43,327
Nope. Nada.

1279
01:04:44,739 --> 01:04:46,536
There's somebody.
Hey! Excuse...

1280
01:04:46,575 --> 01:04:48,406
Dory, Dory, Dory!
Now it's my turn.

1281
01:04:48,443 --> 01:04:50,035
I'm thinking of something
dark and mysterious.

1282
01:04:50,078 --> 01:04:52,444
It's a fish we don't know.
If we ask it directions...

1283
01:04:52,481 --> 01:04:54,506
it could ingest us
and spit out our bones!

1284
01:04:54,549 --> 01:04:57,017
What is it with men
and asking for directions?

1285
01:04:57,052 --> 01:04:58,849
I don't want to play
the gender card right now.

1286
01:04:58,887 --> 01:05:00,821
Let's play
the "Let's Not Die" card.

1287
01:05:00,856 --> 01:05:02,756
- You want to get out of here?
- Of course I do.

1288
01:05:02,791 --> 01:05:06,056
How are we gonna do that
unless we give it a shot?

1289
01:05:06,094 --> 01:05:08,085
Dory, you don't
fully understand...

1290
01:05:08,129 --> 01:05:10,120
Come on. Trust me on this.

1291
01:05:18,206 --> 01:05:22,042
All right.

1292
01:05:22,043 --> 01:05:25,308
Excuse me! Little fella?

1293
01:05:25,347 --> 01:05:29,283
Hello! Don't be rude. Say Hi.

1294
01:05:29,317 --> 01:05:31,342
Ha. Hello.

1295
01:05:31,386 --> 01:05:32,910
- His son Bingo...
- Nemo.

1296
01:05:32,954 --> 01:05:35,980
- Nemo was taken to...
- Sydney.

1297
01:05:36,024 --> 01:05:39,221
Sydney! And it's
really, really important...

1298
01:05:39,261 --> 01:05:41,195
that we get there
as fast as we can...

1299
01:05:41,229 --> 01:05:43,322
so can you help us out?

1300
01:05:43,365 --> 01:05:46,892
Come on, little fella. Come on.

1301
01:05:46,935 --> 01:05:50,166
Dory, I'm a little fella.

1302
01:05:50,205 --> 01:05:53,707
I don't think
that's a little fella.

1303
01:05:53,708 --> 01:05:57,610
Oh! Big fella. Whale. OK.

1304
01:05:57,646 --> 01:06:00,114
Maybe he only speaks whale.

1305
01:06:00,148 --> 01:06:03,379
Mooo! Weee neeed...

1306
01:06:03,418 --> 01:06:07,514
- Dory?
- Tooo fiind his son.

1307
01:06:07,556 --> 01:06:10,218
What are you doing?
Are you sure you speak whale?

1308
01:06:10,258 --> 01:06:13,626
Can youuuu give us
diiirectionsss?

1309
01:06:13,695 --> 01:06:16,027
Dory! Heaven knows
what you're saying!

1310
01:06:16,064 --> 01:06:19,659
- See, he's swimming away.
- Cooome baaack.

1311
01:06:19,701 --> 01:06:21,965
He's not coming back.
You offended him.

1312
01:06:22,003 --> 01:06:23,197
Maybe a different dialect.

1313
01:06:23,238 --> 01:06:26,435
Dory!

1314
01:06:26,474 --> 01:06:29,739
This is not whale.
You're speaking upset stomach.

1315
01:06:29,778 --> 01:06:31,978
- Maybe I should try humpback.
- Don't.

1316
01:06:33,515 --> 01:06:36,484
- You actually sound sick.
- Maybe louder?

1317
01:06:36,518 --> 01:06:37,985
- Rah! Rah!
- Don't do that!

1318
01:06:38,019 --> 01:06:39,748
Too much orca.
Didn't it sound orca-ish?

1319
01:06:39,788 --> 01:06:41,119
It doesn't sound orca.

1320
01:06:41,156 --> 01:06:42,953
It sounds like nothing
I've ever heard.

1321
01:06:45,527 --> 01:06:47,394
It's just as well.
He might be hungry.

1322
01:06:47,495 --> 01:06:50,487
Whales don't eat clownfish.
They eat krill.

1323
01:06:50,532 --> 01:06:54,059
- Swim away!
- Oh, look, krill!

1324
01:06:55,470 --> 01:06:58,940
Move, Dory, move!

1325
01:07:05,046 --> 01:07:07,810
Look at that.
Would you look at that?

1326
01:07:07,849 --> 01:07:11,808
Filthy. Absolutely filthy.

1327
01:07:11,853 --> 01:07:14,845
All thanks to you, kid.
You made it possible.

1328
01:07:14,889 --> 01:07:16,914
Jacques, I said no cleaning.

1329
01:07:17,025 --> 01:07:18,788
I am ashamed.

1330
01:07:18,827 --> 01:07:21,295
Look! Scum angel!

1331
01:07:25,500 --> 01:07:27,434
Bubbles! I love the bubbles!

1332
01:07:29,504 --> 01:07:33,133
Flo? Has anybody seen Flo?

1333
01:07:33,174 --> 01:07:35,802
9:00 and cue dentist.

1334
01:07:35,844 --> 01:07:38,108
Hello, Barbara. Sorry I'm late.

1335
01:07:38,146 --> 01:07:40,842
OK, here we go. Here we go, OK.

1336
01:07:40,882 --> 01:07:42,611
Little Davey Reynolds...

1337
01:07:42,651 --> 01:07:44,243
Walks to the counter,
drops the keys...

1338
01:07:44,285 --> 01:07:46,378
Bloat, that's disgusting!

1339
01:07:46,421 --> 01:07:48,446
Tastes pretty good to me.

1340
01:07:48,490 --> 01:07:50,253
- Urrrp!
- Eww!

1341
01:07:50,291 --> 01:07:53,158
Don't you people realize
we are swimming in our own...

1342
01:07:53,194 --> 01:07:54,286
Here he comes!

1343
01:07:56,331 --> 01:07:59,630
Crikey. What a state.

1344
01:08:01,102 --> 01:08:05,232
Barbara, what's my earliest
appointment tomorrow?

1345
01:08:05,273 --> 01:08:08,208
- 10:00, luv.
- Leave it open, would you?

1346
01:08:08,243 --> 01:08:10,575
I've gotta clean the fish tank
before Darla gets here.

1347
01:08:10,612 --> 01:08:12,705
Did you hear that, Sharkbait?

1348
01:08:12,747 --> 01:08:16,444
Yay! He's gonna clean the tank!

1349
01:08:16,484 --> 01:08:18,247
We're gonna be clean!

1350
01:08:18,286 --> 01:08:19,947
You ready to see your dad, kid?

1351
01:08:19,988 --> 01:08:21,922
Of course you are.

1352
01:08:21,956 --> 01:08:24,584
I wouldn't be surprised
if he's out there...

1353
01:08:24,626 --> 01:08:27,793
in the harbor
waiting for you right now.

1354
01:08:27,896 --> 01:08:30,262
Yeah.

1355
01:09:45,266 --> 01:09:46,995
Here comes the big one.

1356
01:09:47,034 --> 01:09:49,559
Come on! You gotta try this!

1357
01:09:49,604 --> 01:09:52,869
- Will you just stop it?
- Why? What's wrong?

1358
01:09:52,907 --> 01:09:55,205
We're in a whale,
don't you get it?

1359
01:09:55,243 --> 01:09:56,403
- Whale?
- A whale!

1360
01:09:56,444 --> 01:09:59,174
You had to ask for help!
And now we're stuck here!

1361
01:09:59,213 --> 01:10:01,977
A whale. I speak whale.

1362
01:10:02,016 --> 01:10:04,348
No, you're insane!
You can't speak whale!

1363
01:10:04,385 --> 01:10:07,582
I have to get out!
I have to find my son!

1364
01:10:07,622 --> 01:10:13,026
I have to tell him
how old sea turtles are!

1365
01:10:24,038 --> 01:10:26,871
Hey...

1366
01:10:26,908 --> 01:10:29,172
you OK?

1367
01:10:35,249 --> 01:10:38,241
There, there. It's all right.

1368
01:10:38,286 --> 01:10:40,220
It'll be OK.

1369
01:10:40,254 --> 01:10:42,484
No. No, it won't.

1370
01:10:42,523 --> 01:10:44,753
Sure it will. You'll see.

1371
01:10:44,792 --> 01:10:50,924
No. I promised him I'd never
let anything happen to him.

1372
01:10:50,965 --> 01:10:54,366
That's a funny thing
to promise.

1373
01:10:54,402 --> 01:10:55,767
What?

1374
01:10:55,803 --> 01:10:58,237
You can't never let
anything happen to him.

1375
01:10:58,272 --> 01:11:00,706
Then nothing
would ever happen to him.

1376
01:11:03,744 --> 01:11:06,508
Not much fun for little Harpo.

1377
01:11:15,356 --> 01:11:17,187
What's going on?

1378
01:11:17,225 --> 01:11:19,523
Don't know. I'll ask him.

1379
01:11:22,063 --> 01:11:28,093
- Dory...
- Whaaat's goooing onnn?

1380
01:11:34,141 --> 01:11:35,733
I think he says we've stopped.

1381
01:11:35,776 --> 01:11:39,041
Of course we've stopped.
Stop trying to speak whale.

1382
01:11:39,080 --> 01:11:41,878
You'll make things worse.
What is that noise?

1383
01:11:45,987 --> 01:11:48,785
Oh, no. Look what you did.

1384
01:11:48,823 --> 01:11:53,783
The water's going down.
It's going down!

1385
01:11:57,498 --> 01:11:58,931
Really? You sure about that?

1386
01:11:58,966 --> 01:12:01,025
Look! Already it's half empty!

1387
01:12:01,068 --> 01:12:02,831
I'd say it's half full.

1388
01:12:02,870 --> 01:12:04,337
Stop that! It's half empty!

1389
01:12:07,408 --> 01:12:10,605
OK, that one
was a little tougher.

1390
01:12:10,645 --> 01:12:13,514
He either said we should go
to the back of the throat...

1391
01:12:13,581 --> 01:12:15,742
or he wants a root beer float.

1392
01:12:15,783 --> 01:12:17,410
Of course he wants us
to go there!

1393
01:12:17,451 --> 01:12:19,385
That's eating us!

1394
01:12:19,420 --> 01:12:22,389
How do I taste, Moby?
Do I taste good?

1395
01:12:22,423 --> 01:12:24,687
Tell him I'm not interested
in being lunch!

1396
01:12:24,725 --> 01:12:27,193
- OK. Heee...
- Stop talking to him!

1397
01:12:33,367 --> 01:12:34,527
What is going on?

1398
01:12:34,569 --> 01:12:36,867
I'll check. Whaaat...

1399
01:12:36,904 --> 01:12:39,668
No more whale!
You can't speak whale!

1400
01:12:39,707 --> 01:12:42,039
- Yes, I can!
- No, you can't!

1401
01:12:42,076 --> 01:12:45,637
You think you can do these
things, but you can't, Nemo!

1402
01:12:50,651 --> 01:12:53,484
- OK.
- Dory! Oof!

1403
01:12:56,057 --> 01:12:59,652
He says it's time to let go.

1404
01:12:59,694 --> 01:13:01,662
Everything's gonna be
all right.

1405
01:13:01,696 --> 01:13:03,357
How do you know?

1406
01:13:03,397 --> 01:13:06,491
How do you know something bad
isn't gonna happen?

1407
01:13:06,534 --> 01:13:08,434
I don't!

1408
01:13:29,056 --> 01:13:33,823
We're alive!

1409
01:13:34,895 --> 01:13:37,762
Look! Sy-d-ney... Sydney!

1410
01:13:37,798 --> 01:13:40,232
Sydney! Sydney again!

1411
01:13:42,236 --> 01:13:44,704
You were right, Dory!
We made it!

1412
01:13:44,739 --> 01:13:47,674
We're gonna find my son!

1413
01:13:50,244 --> 01:13:53,678
Thaaank yoouuu, sirrr!

1414
01:13:53,781 --> 01:13:56,249
I wish I could speak whale.

1415
01:13:56,283 --> 01:13:58,581
All we gotta do is find
the boat that took him.

1416
01:13:58,619 --> 01:14:01,713
- Right!
- We can do this!

1417
01:14:15,336 --> 01:14:17,634
Morning.

1418
01:14:17,672 --> 01:14:20,937
It's morning, everyone!
Today's the day!

1419
01:14:20,975 --> 01:14:23,136
The sun is shining,
the tank is clean...

1420
01:14:23,177 --> 01:14:26,237
and we are getting out...
The tank is clean.

1421
01:14:26,280 --> 01:14:28,840
The tank is clean!

1422
01:14:28,883 --> 01:14:30,475
But how?

1423
01:14:30,518 --> 01:14:33,214
Boss must've installed it
while we were sleeping.

1424
01:14:33,254 --> 01:14:36,712
- What are we gonna do?
- What's it say, Peach?

1425
01:14:38,092 --> 01:14:39,423
I can't hear you, Peach.

1426
01:14:39,460 --> 01:14:41,894
The Aquascum 2003 is
an all-purpose, self-cleaning...

1427
01:14:41,929 --> 01:14:43,897
maintenance-free,
salt water purifier...

1428
01:14:43,931 --> 01:14:46,923
that is guaranteed to extend
the life of your aquarium fish.

1429
01:14:46,967 --> 01:14:48,195
Stop it!

1430
01:14:48,235 --> 01:14:49,725
The Aquascum
is programmed to scan...

1431
01:14:49,770 --> 01:14:52,068
your tank environment
every five minutes?!

1432
01:14:52,106 --> 01:14:53,801
Scan? What does that mean?

1433
01:14:58,679 --> 01:15:00,180
Temperature... 82 degrees...

1434
01:15:00,281 --> 01:15:01,942
PH balance... normal.

1435
01:15:01,982 --> 01:15:04,382
Nice.

1436
01:15:04,418 --> 01:15:08,980
Curse you, Aquascum!

1437
01:15:09,023 --> 01:15:11,116
That's it for the escape plan.
It's ruined.

1438
01:15:11,158 --> 01:15:12,591
Then what are
we gonna do about...

1439
01:15:12,626 --> 01:15:14,594
Darla!

1440
01:15:14,662 --> 01:15:17,256
Stay down, kid!

1441
01:15:17,298 --> 01:15:19,266
False alarm.

1442
01:15:19,300 --> 01:15:21,393
My nerves can't take
much more of this.

1443
01:15:21,435 --> 01:15:23,665
What'll we do
when that brat gets here?

1444
01:15:23,704 --> 01:15:25,934
- I'm thinking.
- Oh! Gill!

1445
01:15:25,973 --> 01:15:29,136
- Nemo! I'm coming!
- Help me! Help me!

1446
01:15:29,176 --> 01:15:33,078
Swim down! Come on, kid!

1447
01:15:33,114 --> 01:15:34,604
- Everybody jump in!
- Swim down!

1448
01:15:34,648 --> 01:15:35,945
- That's it!
- What the...?

1449
01:15:35,983 --> 01:15:39,248
- Yay!
- Good work!

1450
01:15:39,286 --> 01:15:40,810
Gill!

1451
01:15:40,855 --> 01:15:42,447
- Nemo!
- Sharkbait!

1452
01:15:42,490 --> 01:15:45,891
- Roll, kid!
- Lean! Lean!

1453
01:15:50,364 --> 01:15:52,798
Whoops.
That would've been a nasty fall.

1454
01:15:52,833 --> 01:15:55,427
Gill! Don't let me go belly-up!

1455
01:15:55,469 --> 01:15:57,767
Just calm down, Nemo.
You won't go belly-up.

1456
01:15:57,805 --> 01:16:00,205
I promise. You're gonna be OK.

1457
01:16:03,177 --> 01:16:05,202
Darla!

1458
01:16:08,682 --> 01:16:12,413
Do any of these boats
look familiar to you?

1459
01:16:12,453 --> 01:16:14,353
No, but the boat
has to be here somewhere.

1460
01:16:14,388 --> 01:16:16,515
Come on, Dory.
We're gonna find it.

1461
01:16:16,557 --> 01:16:19,287
I'm totally excited.
Are you excited?

1462
01:16:19,326 --> 01:16:21,089
Dory, wake up.
Wake up, come on.

1463
01:16:21,128 --> 01:16:22,959
Duck!

1464
01:16:22,997 --> 01:16:26,398
That's not a duck.
It's a... pelican!

1465
01:16:35,743 --> 01:16:39,008
No! I didn't come this far
to be breakfast!

1466
01:16:46,520 --> 01:16:48,988
Hey, Nigel.
Would you look at that?

1467
01:16:49,023 --> 01:16:50,388
What? What?

1468
01:16:50,424 --> 01:16:53,291
Sun's barely up and Gerald's
had more than he can handle.

1469
01:16:53,327 --> 01:16:55,955
Yeah. Reckon somebody
ought to help the poor guy.

1470
01:16:55,996 --> 01:16:57,987
Yeah, right. Yeah.

1471
01:16:58,032 --> 01:17:01,661
Don't everybody
fly off at once.

1472
01:17:04,772 --> 01:17:07,707
All right, Gerald.
Fish got your tongue?

1473
01:17:07,741 --> 01:17:10,644
Love a duck!

1474
01:17:10,744 --> 01:17:12,439
I gotta find my son Nemo!

1475
01:17:12,479 --> 01:17:15,573
Nemo? He's that fish!

1476
01:17:15,616 --> 01:17:18,176
The one that's been fighting
the whole ocean!

1477
01:17:18,219 --> 01:17:20,687
I know where your son...

1478
01:17:22,323 --> 01:17:24,018
Wait! Come back! Stop!

1479
01:17:24,058 --> 01:17:26,288
Dory, keep going! He's crazy!

1480
01:17:26,327 --> 01:17:28,090
I got something to tell you!

1481
01:17:32,433 --> 01:17:33,923
Mine.

1482
01:17:38,005 --> 01:17:41,532
Don't make any sudden moves.

1483
01:17:41,575 --> 01:17:45,841
Hop inside my mouth
if you want to live.

1484
01:17:45,880 --> 01:17:49,509
Hop in your mouth?
How does that make me live?

1485
01:17:49,550 --> 01:17:50,710
Mine?

1486
01:17:50,751 --> 01:17:54,385
Because
I can take you to your son.

1487
01:17:54,421 --> 01:17:57,083
- Yeah, right.
- No. I know your son.

1488
01:17:57,124 --> 01:17:59,820
He's orange with
a gimpy fin on one side.

1489
01:17:59,860 --> 01:18:01,020
That's Nemo!

1490
01:18:01,061 --> 01:18:03,723
Mine! Mine! Mine! Mine!

1491
01:18:05,266 --> 01:18:07,757
Fasten your seat belts!

1492
01:18:08,903 --> 01:18:11,030
Mine! Mine! Mine! Mine! Mine!

1493
01:18:11,105 --> 01:18:13,130
Mine! Mine! Mine! Mine!

1494
01:18:29,456 --> 01:18:31,651
Everybody hold on!

1495
01:18:35,029 --> 01:18:37,520
Mine! Mine! Mine! Mine! Mine!

1496
01:18:43,637 --> 01:18:46,265
Too loud! Too loud for me!

1497
01:18:46,307 --> 01:18:48,537
Twinkle, twinkle, little star

1498
01:18:48,575 --> 01:18:51,442
Find a happy place!
Find a happy place!

1499
01:18:51,478 --> 01:18:54,003
Darla, your uncle
will see you now.

1500
01:18:56,050 --> 01:18:58,575
All right, let's see
those pearly whites.

1501
01:18:58,619 --> 01:19:02,919
Raah! I'm a piranha.
They're in the Amazon.

1502
01:19:02,957 --> 01:19:06,393
And a piranha's a fish,
just like your present.

1503
01:19:07,761 --> 01:19:09,524
I get fishy, fishy

1504
01:19:09,563 --> 01:19:12,657
Oh, no. Poor little guy.

1505
01:19:12,700 --> 01:19:14,531
- He's dead.
- Sharkbait!

1506
01:19:14,568 --> 01:19:15,762
Yay! Fishy, fishy, fishy!

1507
01:19:15,803 --> 01:19:17,395
Must've left your present
in the car, sweetie.

1508
01:19:17,438 --> 01:19:19,736
I'll go and get it.

1509
01:19:19,773 --> 01:19:21,502
- He's still alive!
- He's not dead!

1510
01:19:21,542 --> 01:19:23,567
What's happening?
Why is he playing dead?

1511
01:19:23,610 --> 01:19:25,475
He's gonna get flushed
down the toilet.

1512
01:19:25,512 --> 01:19:27,912
- He's gonna get out of here!
- He's gonna get flushed!

1513
01:19:27,948 --> 01:19:29,711
What a smart little guy!

1514
01:19:29,750 --> 01:19:31,308
Oh, no! Not the trash can!

1515
01:19:31,352 --> 01:19:32,649
Nemo! No!

1516
01:19:32,686 --> 01:19:36,087
- Hey! I found his dad!
- Where's Nemo?

1517
01:19:36,123 --> 01:19:37,488
- Dentist!
- He's over there!

1518
01:19:37,524 --> 01:19:40,925
What's a dentist?
Nigel, get in there!

1519
01:19:40,961 --> 01:19:44,920
- I can't go in there!
- Yes, you can! Charge!

1520
01:19:46,400 --> 01:19:47,924
What the...?

1521
01:19:49,203 --> 01:19:51,797
Darla, sweetie, look out!

1522
01:19:55,209 --> 01:19:57,370
Hold still!

1523
01:19:57,411 --> 01:19:59,345
Easy! Easy!

1524
01:20:00,647 --> 01:20:01,875
Hold still!

1525
01:20:01,915 --> 01:20:05,078
Nobody's going to hurt you!
Oof!

1526
01:20:11,158 --> 01:20:13,558
Nemo.

1527
01:20:13,594 --> 01:20:14,856
Oh, my goodness.

1528
01:20:14,895 --> 01:20:16,795
Gotcha! Keep down!

1529
01:20:16,830 --> 01:20:18,092
Nemo!

1530
01:20:18,132 --> 01:20:19,861
Daddy?

1531
01:20:19,900 --> 01:20:23,734
Out with you! And stay out!

1532
01:20:23,771 --> 01:20:25,102
Daddy?

1533
01:20:25,139 --> 01:20:26,538
Fishy?

1534
01:20:26,573 --> 01:20:29,701
Fishy! Wake up!

1535
01:20:29,743 --> 01:20:30,903
Oh, no!

1536
01:20:30,944 --> 01:20:33,469
To the top of
Mount Wannahockaloogie!

1537
01:20:33,514 --> 01:20:35,914
Why are you sleeping?

1538
01:20:35,949 --> 01:20:38,383
- Hurry!
- Bloat!

1539
01:20:41,455 --> 01:20:43,548
Ring of Fire!

1540
01:20:44,558 --> 01:20:48,119
Fishy!

1541
01:20:49,596 --> 01:20:51,655
Crikey! All the animals
have gone mad!

1542
01:20:53,467 --> 01:20:56,027
Aaah! Get it out!

1543
01:20:56,070 --> 01:20:58,630
- Smack her in the head!
- Go, Gill, go!

1544
01:20:58,672 --> 01:21:00,663
Fish in my hair!

1545
01:21:00,707 --> 01:21:02,072
Gill!

1546
01:21:02,109 --> 01:21:06,603
Sharkbait...
tell your dad I said hi.

1547
01:21:11,652 --> 01:21:12,914
Go get 'em!

1548
01:21:17,925 --> 01:21:19,654
- He did it!
- Yay!

1549
01:21:19,693 --> 01:21:22,628
- I'm so happy!
- Is he gonna be OK, Gill?

1550
01:21:22,663 --> 01:21:24,893
Don't worry.
All drains lead to the ocean.

1551
01:21:24,932 --> 01:21:26,661
Fishy!

1552
01:21:34,208 --> 01:21:36,540
Daddy!

1553
01:22:12,346 --> 01:22:15,179
I'm so sorry.

1554
01:22:16,350 --> 01:22:17,817
Truly, I am.

1555
01:22:17,818 --> 01:22:18,648
Truly, I am.

1556
01:22:36,003 --> 01:22:38,198
- Hey.
- Dory...

1557
01:22:38,238 --> 01:22:40,297
if it wasn't for you...

1558
01:22:40,340 --> 01:22:43,138
I never would've even
made it here.

1559
01:22:43,177 --> 01:22:45,168
So, thank you.

1560
01:22:47,281 --> 01:22:49,010
Hey, wait a minute.

1561
01:22:49,049 --> 01:22:51,609
Wait. Where are you going?

1562
01:22:51,652 --> 01:22:55,213
It's over, Dory.
We were too late.

1563
01:22:55,255 --> 01:23:00,022
Nemo's gone,
and I'm going home now.

1564
01:23:00,060 --> 01:23:02,551
No. No, you can't.

1565
01:23:04,398 --> 01:23:06,161
Stop!

1566
01:23:07,768 --> 01:23:09,531
Please don't go away.

1567
01:23:09,570 --> 01:23:11,504
Please?

1568
01:23:11,538 --> 01:23:14,302
No one's ever stuck with me
for so long before.

1569
01:23:14,341 --> 01:23:17,902
And if you leave, I just...

1570
01:23:17,945 --> 01:23:19,879
I remember things
better with you.

1571
01:23:19,913 --> 01:23:22,905
I do. Look... P. Sherman, 42...

1572
01:23:22,950 --> 01:23:25,885
42...

1573
01:23:25,919 --> 01:23:28,683
I remember it.
I do. It's there.

1574
01:23:28,722 --> 01:23:30,815
I know it is because
when I look at you...

1575
01:23:30,857 --> 01:23:32,290
I can feel it.

1576
01:23:32,326 --> 01:23:38,128
I look at you
and I... I'm home.

1577
01:23:39,967 --> 01:23:41,559
Please...

1578
01:23:41,602 --> 01:23:44,230
I don't want that to go away.

1579
01:23:44,271 --> 01:23:46,637
I don't want to forget.

1580
01:23:47,975 --> 01:23:52,036
I'm sorry, Dory, but I do.

1581
01:24:03,323 --> 01:24:06,588
- Manna from heaven.
- Sweet nectar of life!

1582
01:24:06,627 --> 01:24:08,686
Hey! Hey! Hey!

1583
01:24:08,729 --> 01:24:12,130
- This is our spot!
- Get outta here!

1584
01:24:13,467 --> 01:24:15,560
Hey! Hey! Hey!

1585
01:24:15,669 --> 01:24:17,136
Yeah, that's it, fella.

1586
01:24:17,170 --> 01:24:18,797
Just keep on swimmin'.
You got that.

1587
01:24:18,839 --> 01:24:20,864
Too right, mate!

1588
01:24:20,907 --> 01:24:22,204
Oh! I got a live one here!

1589
01:24:22,242 --> 01:24:23,675
Have you seen my dad?

1590
01:24:23,710 --> 01:24:25,940
Gotcha! Hey! Hey!
Come back here!

1591
01:24:25,979 --> 01:24:27,469
You let him go!

1592
01:24:27,514 --> 01:24:29,649
Hey! Hey!

1593
01:24:29,650 --> 01:24:34,144
Dad! Dad!

1594
01:24:34,187 --> 01:24:35,814
Dad!

1595
01:24:49,202 --> 01:24:52,262
Excuse me.

1596
01:24:52,306 --> 01:24:53,534
Are you all right?

1597
01:24:53,573 --> 01:24:56,201
I don't know where I am.
I don't know what's going on.

1598
01:24:56,243 --> 01:24:59,110
I think I lost somebody,
but I can't remember.

1599
01:24:59,146 --> 01:25:03,242
It's OK.
I'm looking for someone, too.

1600
01:25:03,283 --> 01:25:05,717
Hey, we can look together.

1601
01:25:05,752 --> 01:25:08,084
I'm Dory.

1602
01:25:08,121 --> 01:25:09,281
I'm Nemo.

1603
01:25:09,323 --> 01:25:12,690
Nemo? That's a nice name.

1604
01:25:21,635 --> 01:25:24,570
- Dad!
- Dad!

1605
01:25:24,604 --> 01:25:26,663
Wait a minute.
Is it your dad or my dad?

1606
01:25:26,707 --> 01:25:29,175
- My dad.
- Got it. Dad!

1607
01:25:29,209 --> 01:25:31,473
- Where are we, anyway?
- Dad! Dad!

1608
01:25:31,511 --> 01:25:35,413
Oh. Syl... Shi... Sydney.

1609
01:25:35,449 --> 01:25:39,715
P. Sherman,
42 Wallaby Way, Sydney.

1610
01:25:39,753 --> 01:25:41,516
Nemo!

1611
01:25:41,555 --> 01:25:43,921
It's you! You're Nemo!

1612
01:25:43,957 --> 01:25:45,618
Yes, yes, I'm Nemo!

1613
01:25:45,659 --> 01:25:48,253
You're Nemo!
You were dead. I saw you.

1614
01:25:48,295 --> 01:25:50,195
And here you are! I found you.

1615
01:25:50,230 --> 01:25:52,960
You're not dead.
And your father... Your father!

1616
01:25:52,999 --> 01:25:55,365
You know my father?!
Where is he?

1617
01:25:55,402 --> 01:25:58,235
This way!
He went this way. Quick!

1618
01:25:58,271 --> 01:25:59,898
Hey, hey, hey!

1619
01:25:59,940 --> 01:26:01,100
Hey! Hey!

1620
01:26:01,141 --> 01:26:02,631
Have you seen
an orange fish swim by?

1621
01:26:02,676 --> 01:26:05,042
- It looks just like him!
- But bigger!

1622
01:26:05,078 --> 01:26:06,306
Yeah, I saw him, bluey.

1623
01:26:06,346 --> 01:26:07,813
But I'm not tellin' you
where he went...

1624
01:26:07,848 --> 01:26:13,386
and there's no way
you're gonna make me.

1625
01:26:13,387 --> 01:26:14,547
Mine.

1626
01:26:14,654 --> 01:26:17,418
All right! I'll talk!

1627
01:26:17,457 --> 01:26:24,163
He went to the fishing grounds!

1628
01:26:24,164 --> 01:26:26,029
Hey, look out!

1629
01:26:26,066 --> 01:26:28,557
I'm sorry.
I'm just trying to get home.

1630
01:26:29,603 --> 01:26:33,334
Dad! Dad!

1631
01:26:33,373 --> 01:26:34,772
Nemo?

1632
01:26:34,808 --> 01:26:37,276
- Daddy!
- Nemo?

1633
01:26:37,310 --> 01:26:39,279
- Dad!
- Nemo's alive!

1634
01:26:39,346 --> 01:26:41,337
Dory? Nemo!

1635
01:26:41,381 --> 01:26:42,575
Daddy!

1636
01:26:42,616 --> 01:26:44,914
Nemo! I'm coming, Nemo!

1637
01:26:44,951 --> 01:26:48,614
- Dad!
- Nemo! Thank goodness.

1638
01:26:48,655 --> 01:26:51,590
It's all right, son.
It's gonna be OK.

1639
01:26:51,625 --> 01:26:54,494
Turn around!
You're going the wrong way!

1640
01:26:56,997 --> 01:26:58,362
Look out!

1641
01:26:58,398 --> 01:27:01,026
Oh, my...

1642
01:27:17,751 --> 01:27:21,312
Help! He-e-elp!

1643
01:27:21,354 --> 01:27:22,946
- Dory!
- Come on!

1644
01:27:22,989 --> 01:27:24,388
Help! Help!

1645
01:27:24,424 --> 01:27:27,154
Help! Get us out!

1646
01:27:27,194 --> 01:27:28,991
No, no, no! Dory!

1647
01:27:29,029 --> 01:27:32,021
- Dad, I know what to do!
- Nemo! No!

1648
01:27:32,065 --> 01:27:34,795
We have to tell all the fish
to swim down together!

1649
01:27:34,835 --> 01:27:37,531
- Get out of there now!
- I know this will work!

1650
01:27:37,571 --> 01:27:39,505
No, I am not
gonna lose you again!

1651
01:27:39,539 --> 01:27:42,975
There's no time!
It's the only way to save Dory!

1652
01:27:44,277 --> 01:27:45,744
I can do this.

1653
01:27:46,913 --> 01:27:49,040
You're right.

1654
01:27:49,082 --> 01:27:50,913
I know you can.

1655
01:27:50,951 --> 01:27:53,852
- Lucky fin!
- Now, go! Hurry!

1656
01:27:53,887 --> 01:27:56,685
Tell all the fish to swim down!

1657
01:27:56,723 --> 01:28:00,090
Well? You heard my son!
Come on!

1658
01:28:01,595 --> 01:28:04,223
Dory, you have
to tell everybody to...

1659
01:28:04,264 --> 01:28:05,788
Swim down together!

1660
01:28:05,832 --> 01:28:08,096
Do you understand
what I'm saying to you?

1661
01:28:08,134 --> 01:28:10,398
Swim down!

1662
01:28:14,741 --> 01:28:15,969
Everybody swim down!

1663
01:28:16,009 --> 01:28:18,534
Come on, you have to swim down!

1664
01:28:18,578 --> 01:28:21,274
Down! Swim down!

1665
01:28:23,383 --> 01:28:27,012
Swim down! Swim down!

1666
01:28:34,728 --> 01:28:37,128
Don't give up! Keep swimming!

1667
01:28:37,163 --> 01:28:39,597
Just keep swimming!

1668
01:28:43,837 --> 01:28:45,464
That's it!

1669
01:28:48,408 --> 01:28:50,399
It's working!

1670
01:28:52,846 --> 01:28:55,872
Keep swimming! Keep swimming!

1671
01:28:55,916 --> 01:28:58,043
Just keep swimming!
Keep swimming!

1672
01:28:58,084 --> 01:28:59,551
Come on, Dad!

1673
01:28:59,586 --> 01:29:02,077
- You're doing great, son!
- That's my dad.

1674
01:29:02,122 --> 01:29:04,420
Let's get to the bottom!
Keep swimming!

1675
01:29:04,457 --> 01:29:06,982
Just keep swimming,
just keep swimming

1676
01:29:07,027 --> 01:29:09,222
Almost there! Keep swimming!

1677
01:29:12,799 --> 01:29:14,130
Keep swimming!

1678
01:29:16,436 --> 01:29:17,562
Keep swimming!

1679
01:29:27,981 --> 01:29:29,448
- Oof!
- Hey!

1680
01:29:29,482 --> 01:29:33,077
- Dory! Where's Nemo?
- There!

1681
01:29:34,788 --> 01:29:37,848
Oh, no. Nemo!

1682
01:29:43,797 --> 01:29:45,697
Nemo?

1683
01:29:47,367 --> 01:29:49,665
Nemo?

1684
01:29:49,703 --> 01:29:53,696
It's OK. Daddy's here.
Daddy's got you.

1685
01:29:58,144 --> 01:29:59,304
Daddy?

1686
01:29:59,346 --> 01:30:00,870
Oh, thank goodness.

1687
01:30:00,914 --> 01:30:04,611
Dad... I don't hate you.

1688
01:30:04,651 --> 01:30:06,482
Oh, no, no, no.

1689
01:30:06,519 --> 01:30:09,181
I'm so sorry, Nemo.

1690
01:30:18,431 --> 01:30:21,298
- Hey, guess what?
- What?

1691
01:30:21,334 --> 01:30:24,826
Sea turtles... I met one.

1692
01:30:24,871 --> 01:30:29,069
And he was 150 years old.

1693
01:30:29,109 --> 01:30:33,273
- 150?
- Yep.

1694
01:30:33,313 --> 01:30:38,148
Sandy Plankton said
they only live to be 100.

1695
01:30:38,184 --> 01:30:39,742
Sandy Plankton?

1696
01:30:39,786 --> 01:30:41,777
Do you think I would
cross the entire ocean...

1697
01:30:41,821 --> 01:30:43,914
and not know as much
as Sandy Plankton?

1698
01:30:43,957 --> 01:30:46,619
He was 150! Not 100!

1699
01:30:46,660 --> 01:30:50,528
Who is this Sandy Plankton
who knows everything?

1700
01:30:52,232 --> 01:30:55,832
Time for school!
Get up! Let's go!

1701
01:30:55,869 --> 01:30:58,963
- I'm gonna win!
- No, you're not!

1702
01:30:59,005 --> 01:31:02,771
- I did it!
- Aw, my own son beats me!

1703
01:31:02,809 --> 01:31:05,277
Climb aboard, explorers.

1704
01:31:05,311 --> 01:31:08,439
The sea cucumber looks over
to the mollusk and says...

1705
01:31:08,481 --> 01:31:11,348
"With fronds like these,
who needs anemones?"

1706
01:31:13,053 --> 01:31:15,283
Hello, Nemo. Who's this?

1707
01:31:15,388 --> 01:31:18,846
- Exchange student.
- I'm from the E.A.C., dude!

1708
01:31:18,892 --> 01:31:21,520
- Sweet!
- Totally.

1709
01:31:21,561 --> 01:31:23,529
Seriously, Marty.

1710
01:31:23,563 --> 01:31:25,531
Did you really do all
the things you say you did?

1711
01:31:25,565 --> 01:31:27,260
Pardon me.

1712
01:31:27,300 --> 01:31:29,996
Hello.

1713
01:31:30,036 --> 01:31:31,697
Don't be alarmed.

1714
01:31:31,738 --> 01:31:35,504
We wanted to make sure our
newest member got home safely.

1715
01:31:35,542 --> 01:31:37,874
- Thanks, guys.
- See you next week.

1716
01:31:37,911 --> 01:31:41,369
- Keep up with the program.
- Remember, fish are friends...

1717
01:31:41,414 --> 01:31:43,780
Not food! Bye!

1718
01:31:43,817 --> 01:31:45,682
Hold on, here we go!

1719
01:31:45,719 --> 01:31:47,414
Next stop... knowledge!

1720
01:31:47,454 --> 01:31:49,922
Bye, son! Have fun!

1721
01:31:49,956 --> 01:31:51,253
Bye, Dad!

1722
01:31:51,291 --> 01:31:54,727
Oh! Mr. Ray, wait.
I forgot something.

1723
01:31:59,399 --> 01:32:02,027
Love you, Dad.

1724
01:32:02,068 --> 01:32:04,059
I love you, too, son.

1725
01:32:06,339 --> 01:32:09,740
Dad? You can let go now.

1726
01:32:09,776 --> 01:32:13,507
Sorry. Go have an adventure.

1727
01:32:13,546 --> 01:32:15,776
Good-bye! See ya later, dudes!

1728
01:32:15,882 --> 01:32:18,316
- Bye, Elmo!
- Nemo.

1729
01:32:18,351 --> 01:32:21,809
- Bye, Nemo!
- See you after school, Dory!

1730
01:32:21,855 --> 01:32:24,755
Bye, Dad!

1731
01:32:24,758 --> 01:32:26,851
Bye, son.

1732
01:32:43,877 --> 01:32:46,869
Barbara, I don't understand it.

1733
01:32:46,913 --> 01:32:49,279
Here this thing has
a lifetime guarantee...

1734
01:32:49,315 --> 01:32:50,543
and it breaks!

1735
01:32:50,583 --> 01:32:52,881
I had to clean the tank myself,
take all the fish out...

1736
01:32:52,919 --> 01:32:55,285
put 'em in bags, and...

1737
01:32:55,321 --> 01:32:57,812
Where'd the fish go?

1738
01:33:02,662 --> 01:33:04,391
- Come on, Peach!
- Hurry!

1739
01:33:04,430 --> 01:33:06,261
- You can do it!
- That's it.

1740
01:33:06,299 --> 01:33:07,732
Just a little further.

1741
01:33:07,767 --> 01:33:09,997
That's the shortest
red light I've ever seen!

1742
01:33:10,036 --> 01:33:12,266
Come on, Peach!

1743
01:33:21,614 --> 01:33:23,411
Now what?

1744
01:33:30,915 --> 01:33:34,043
Somewhere

1745
01:33:34,085 --> 01:33:36,246
Beyond the sea

1746
01:33:36,287 --> 01:33:41,418
Somewhere, waitin' for me

1747
01:33:41,459 --> 01:33:46,396
My lover stands on golden sands

1748
01:33:46,431 --> 01:33:48,831
And watches the ships

1749
01:33:48,867 --> 01:33:52,894
That go sailin'

1750
01:33:52,937 --> 01:33:55,872
Somewhere

1751
01:33:55,907 --> 01:33:58,239
Beyond the sea

1752
01:33:58,276 --> 01:34:03,373
She's there watchin' for me

1753
01:34:03,414 --> 01:34:08,249
if I could fly
like birds on high

1754
01:34:08,286 --> 01:34:10,982
Then straight to her arms

1755
01:34:11,022 --> 01:34:14,685
I'll go sailin'

1756
01:34:14,726 --> 01:34:17,786
It's far

1757
01:34:17,829 --> 01:34:20,491
Beyond the stars

1758
01:34:20,532 --> 01:34:24,468
It's near, beyond the moon

1759
01:34:25,470 --> 01:34:28,906
I know

1760
01:34:28,940 --> 01:34:31,067
Beyond a doubt

1761
01:34:31,109 --> 01:34:33,077
